teroid belt"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Julie's Survival and Escape","status":"active","characters":["Julie Mao","Captain Darren","Dave","Mike","Wan Li"],"summary":"Julie remains missing, with no new developments in her survival status. The Scopuli's eerie silence and the attackers' methods continue to hint at a larger conspiracy tied to her disappearance."},{"name":"The Scopuli's Attack and Abduction","status":"active","characters":["Julie Mao","The Attackers","Dave","Captain Darren","Mike","Wan Li","Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton","Shed Garvey"],"summary":"Holden's team investigates the Scopuli, discovering a breaching charge, a fake distress beacon, and evidence of intentional reactor shutdown. The ship's empty state and the attackers' precise actions suggest a deliberate cover-up, deepening the mystery of the crew's disappearance."},{"name":"The Biotech Entity in Engineering","status":"dormant","characters":["Julie Mao","Captain Darren"],"summary":"The biotech entity arc is paused as the chapter focuses on Holden's investigation. The entity's connection to the Scopuli's attack remains unexplored, but the fake beacon and reactor shutdown suggest a possible link to the attackers' motives."}],"summary":"Holden and his crew aboard the Knight investigate the wrecked Scopuli, discovering a breaching charge and a fake distress beacon. The ship's reactor was manually shut down after an attack, with all pressure doors opened to purge the atmosphere. The asteroid CA-2216862's gravity likely played a role in the Scopuli's positioning, leaving the crew with more questions than answers."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":8,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Julie Mao","aliases":["Juliette Andromeda Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the