ite of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"The Scopuli's Attack and Abduction","description":"A retooled colony transport ship hauling ice between Saturn's rings and the asteroid belt.","recentEvents":"Holden and his crew prepare to investigate the wrecked Scopuli, departing from the Canterbury after final checks.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"Martian Navy Involvement and Scopuli's Attack","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Eros","description":"A celestial body serving as the home port of the damaged Martian freighter.","recentEvents":"The freighter, registered to Eros, sent an emergency signal requiring aid.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"Martian Navy Involvement and Scopuli's Attack","description":"A massive space station in the asteroid belt, serving as a hub for trade and conflict between Belters and Earthlings.","recentEvents":"Miller and his team quell a riot sparked by Holden's broadcast about a Martian battery, confronting OPA agents and a violent mob.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passe