lationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"The Scopuli's Attack and Abduction","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew debates their next move, receives orders to travel to Jupiter, and prepares to evade pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target of their flight path"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"Martian Navy Involvement and Scopuli's Attack","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Eros","description":"A celestial body serving as the home port of the damaged Martian freighter.","recentEvents":"The freighter, registered to Eros, sent an emergency signal requiring aid.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"Martian Navy Involvement and Scopuli's Attack","description":"A massive space station in the asteroid belt, serving as a hub for trade and conflict between Belters and Earthlings.","recentEvents":"Miller and his team quell a riot sparked by Holden's broadcast about a Martian battery, confronting OPA agents and a violent mob.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager"],"description":"A Martian Congressional Republic Navy battleship dispatched to intercept the Knight.","recentEvents":"Ordered to pick up the Knight crew, with a 13-day arrival window.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Julie's Survival and Escape","status":"active","characters":["Julie Mao","The Attackers"],"summary":"The Scopuli's mysterious shutdown and cryptic messages persist, with no new clues about Julie's fate. The attackers' advanced tech suggests a coordinated, state-sponsored operation."},{"name":"Martian Navy Involvement and Scopuli's Attack","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Captain Shaddid","Detective Miller","Dmitri Havelock"],"summary":"A cryptic emergency message from Holden near Saturn hints at a larger crisis, linking to the Scopuli's mysterious shutdown and the unresolved disappearance of the crew. The message's potential leak threatens to escalate tensions across the Belt."},{"name":"The Scopuli's Attack and Abduction","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Alex Kamal","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"Holden discovers Martian Navy serial numbers on recovered tech, implicating the Martian military in the Scopuli attack. He prepares to broadcast evidence of the stealth ship's involvement, risking escalation of Belt-wide tensions."}],"summary":"Holden's crew aboard the Knight faces a dilemma after receiving conflicting orders from P and K to head to Jupiter, where the MCRN Donnager will intercept them. Tensions rise as they navigate toward the gas giant while evading unknown pursuers in the asteroid Belt, with the Martian government's involvement complicating their escape plan."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":12,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Julie Mao","aliases":["Juliette Andromeda Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Miller accessed her digital files, discovered personal correspondence and OPA affiliations"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Commander and close ally"},{"ch