nce.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Julie's Survival and Escape","status":"dormant","characters":["Julie Mao","Detective Miller"],"summary":"Miller's investigation stalls as focus shifts to the Donnager crisis, leaving Julie's disappearance and potential OPA ties unresolved."},{"name":"OPA's Protective Role and Belt Security Crisis","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","OPA Man","Martian Navy"],"summary":"The Donnager's torpedo threat and the Belt ships' survival challenge assumptions about OPA's protective role. Miller's investigation into OPA's dual nature intersects with the Martian Navy's aggressive stance, complicating the Belt's security dilemma."},{"name":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","status":"active","characters":["OPA","Martian Congressional Republic","Belters","Detective Miller"],"summary":"Miller discovers the OPA is actively countering inner-planet economic exploitation of Belters, not merely engaging in criminal activity. This revelation complicates the security crisis, as the OPA's actions blur lines between protection and oppression, with implications for Julie's disappearance and the Belt's stability."},{"name":"Martian Navy, OPA, and Belt Security Crisis","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Lieutenant Lopez","Captain Theresa Yao"],"summary":"The Donnager's confrontation with Belt ships escalates tensions, revealing Martian military readiness to destroy Belt vessels. Holden's interrogation highlights suspicions about his past actions, while the torpedo attack and close-quarters combat demonstrate the volatile standoff between Mars and the Belt."}],"summary":"Holden's crew is detained aboard the Martian battleship Donnager after docking, where they face interrogation over their connection to the pursuing 