 death."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Superior officer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Diagnosed and repaired the Knight's landing gear, interacted with Holden and Amos Burton."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Assisted Naomi Nagata with a damaged cable on the hangar deck."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated with Dawes to continue searching for Julie, realized the Scopuli's connection to the Canterbury incident, and decided to involve Havelock in his investigation."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Assigned Miller to investigate a hardware shop extortion case, dismissed conspiracy theories about Mars."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Guided the Knight into the Donnager's docking bay and participated in the tense standoff with the Martian military."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided information about Havelock's presence at the Blue Frog and facilitated Miller's encounter with him."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Contacted via comm"}],"recentEv