 a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Julie's Survival and Escape","status":"dormant","characters":["Julie Mao","Detective Miller"],"summary":"Miller's investigation stalls as focus shifts to the Donnager crisis, leaving Julie's disappearance and potential OPA ties unresolved."},{"name":"OPA's Protective Role and Belt Security Crisis","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","OPA Man","Martian Navy"],"summary":"The Donnager's torpedo threat and the Belt ships' survival challenge assumptions about OPA's protective role. Miller's investigation into OPA's dual nature intersects with the Martian Navy's aggressive stance, complicating the Belt's security dilemma."},{"name":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","status":"active","characters":["OPA","Martian Congressional Republic","Belters","Detective Miller"],"summary":"Miller discovers the OPA is actively countering inner-planet economic exploitation of Belters, not merely engaging in criminal activity. This revelation complicates the security crisis, as the OPA's actions blur lines between protection and oppression, with implications for Julie's disappearance and the Belt's stability."},{"name":"Martian Navy, OPA, and Belt Security Crisis","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Lieutenant Lopez","Captain Theresa Yao"],"summary":"The Donnager's confrontation with Belt ships escalates tensions, revealing Martian military readiness to destroy Belt vessels. Holden's interrogation highlights suspicions about his past actions, while the torpedo attack and close-quarters combat demonstrate the volatile standoff between Mars and the Belt."}],"summary":"Detective Miller investigates Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating escalating Belt-Mars tensions. The OPA's liaison warns of impending war, citing attacks like Phoebe Station's destruction. Miller uncovers connections between Mao's last known location, the Scopuli freighter, and the Canterbury massacre, complicating his search for her."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":17,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Julie Mao","aliases":["Juliette Andromeda Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Miller accessed her digital files, discovered personal correspondence and OPA affiliations"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate a