bury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Commander and close ally"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Docked with the Donnager, interrogated by Lieutenant Lopez, survived a torpedo attack, and witnessed Shed Garvey's death."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Superior officer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Diagnosed and repaired the Knight's landing gear, interacted with Holden and Amos Burton."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Assisted Naomi Nagata with a damaged cable on the hangar deck."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated with Dawes to continue searching for Julie, realized the Scopuli's connection to the Canterbury incident, and decided to involve Havelock in his investigation."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Assigned Miller to investigate a hardware shop extortion case, dismissed conspiracy theories about Mars."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Guided the Knight into the Donnager's docking bay and participated in the tense standoff with the Martian military."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided information about Havelock's presence at the Blue Frog and facilitated Miller's encounter with him."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Contacted via comm"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a comm message warning Holden about potential Martian coercion and offering assistance."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Confronted Miller about stopping the search for Julie Mao, revealed she was on the Scopuli freighter linked to the Canterbury incident, and attempted to form an alliance for stability."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Protective Role and Belt Security Crisis","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Eros","description":"A celestial body serving as the home port of the damaged Martian freighter.","recentEvents":"The freighter, registered to Eros, sent an emergency signal requiring aid.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"Martian Navy, OPA, and Belt Security Crisis","description":"A massive space station in the asteroid belt, serving as a hub for trade and conflict between Belters and Earthlings.","recentEvents":"Miller and his team quell a riot sparked by Holden's broadcast about a Martian battery, confronting OPA agents and a violent mob.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation."