 stolen transponder code to hide the Tachi's identity."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Superior officer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Treated Amos Burton's injuries, handled Kelly's burial, and communicated with Fred Johnson about the transponder code."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Suffered a compound fracture to his leg, treated by Naomi Nagata, and stabilized."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Investigated murder of Enrique Dos Santos, discussed Juliette Mao case with Shaddid, met Anderson Dawes for information exchange"},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed Martian navy's role in Canterbury incident, denied Miller's request for Holden's debriefing transcripts"},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Piloted the Tachi, coordinated with Holden to avoid detection, and handled Kelly's burial."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided information about Havelock's presence at the Blue Frog and facilitated Miller's encounter with him."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a transponder code and coordinates to help the Tachi avoid detection."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Provided evidence of riot gear diversion to organized crime, agreed to assist in Juliette Mao search"},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Ex-cop from three generations in the Belt with hardened attitude toward violence","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Assisted Miller with murder investigation, tracked down perpetrators of camera sabotage"},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Eros","description":"A celestial body serving as the home port of the damaged Martian freighter.","recentEvents":"The freighter, registered to Eros, sent an emergency signal requiring aid.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive space station in the asteroid belt, serving as a hub for trade and conflict between Belters and Earthlings.","recentEvents":"Detective Miller investigates the murder of Enrique Dos Santos, whose body was displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works. The incident sparks tensions between Martian authorities and Belters.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","status":"active","characters":["Fred Johnson","Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"The OPA's covert operations continue as Holden leverages Fred Johnson's network to hide the Tachi, revealing the organization's ability to manipulate Martian registries and provide sanctuary for Belters. The data cube from Lieutenant Kelly hints at deeper OPA involvement in the Donnager's destruction."},{"name":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Captain Shaddid","Martian Navy"],"summary":"The Martian Navy's pursuit of the Tachi escalates tensions, while Holden's crew navigates the moral ambiguity of using OPA resources to evade capture. The conflict between Martian control and Belt autonomy remains unresolved, with the OPA serving as both adversary and reluctant ally."},{"name":"Martian Navy, OPA, and Belt Security Crisis","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal","Fred Johnson","Detective Miller"],"summary":"Holden's crew escapes the Donnager after a violent boarding action, using a stolen Martian warship (Tachi) and a forged transponder code provided by Fred Johnson. The crew now faces the challenge of evading Martian detection while dealing with casualties and the ethical weight of their actions."}],"summary":"Holden and his crew survive a deadly boarding action on the MCRN Donnager, escaping to the Tachi where they tend to the wounded and bury Lieutenant Kelly. With a stolen Martian warship, they seek safe harbor through a covert transponder code provided by Fred Johnson, now en route to a hidden location. The crew grapples with loss and uncertainty as they evade pursuit."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":20,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Julie Mao","aliases":["Juliette Andromeda Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Miller accessed her digital files, discovered personal correspondence and OPA affiliations"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Commander and close ally"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Survived a battle on the Donnager, coordinated evacuation, and planned to use a stolen transponder code to hide the Tachi's identity."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Superior officer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Treated Amos Burton's injuries, handled Kelly's burial, and communicated with Fred Johnson about the transponder code."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Suffered a compound fracture to his leg, treated by Naomi Nagata, and stabilized."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned from the Mao case, confronted political tensions on Ceres, and faced personal conflict over Julie's safety."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Piloted the Tachi, coordinated with Holden to avoid detection, and handled Kelly's burial."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a transponder code and coordinates to help the Tachi avoid detection."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Ex-cop from three generations in the Belt with hardened attitude toward violence","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed case assignments with Miller, hinted at systemic issues in the station's justice system."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Eros","description":"A celestial body serving as the home port of the damaged Martian freighter.","recentEvents":"The freighter, registered to Eros, sent an emergency signal requiring aid.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive space station in the asteroid belt, serving as a hub for trade and conflict between Belters and Earthlings.","recentEvents":"Detective Miller investigates the murder of Enrique Dos Santos, whose body was displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works. The incident sparks tensions between Martian authorities and Belters.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]"}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","status":"active","characters":["Fred Johnson","Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"The OPA's covert operations continue as Holden leverages Fred Johnson's network to hide the Tachi, revealing the organization's ability to manipulate Martian registries and provide sanctuary for Belters. The data cube from Lieutenant Kelly hints at deeper OPA involvement in the Donnager's destruction."},{"name":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Captain Shaddid","Martian Navy","Anderson Dawes"],"summary":"The Martian Congressional Republic officially declares war on the Belt, framing the OPA as the aggressor. Miller's investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance is sidelined as the OPA and Martian Navy escalate hostilities, with Holden's crew now in OPA custody and the station becoming a frontline zone."},{"name":"Martian Navy, OPA, and Belt Security Crisis","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal","Fred Johnson","Detective Miller"],"summary":"Holden's crew escapes the Donnager after a violent boarding action, using a stolen Martian warship (Tachi) and a forged transponder code provided by Fred Johnson. The crew now faces the challenge of evading Martian detection while dealing with casualties and the ethical weight of their actions."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","status":"active","characters":["Anderson Dawes","Captain Shaddid","Detective Miller","Juliette Mao"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism threatens to erupt into civil war as Dawes asserts control over Holden's case, revealing the OPA's covert involvement in the Donnager's destruction and their strategic manipulation of Martian-Mars tensions to protect Belt interests."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Conflict and Julie's Fate [active]","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Juliette Mao","Hasini","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"Miller confronts his failure to protect Julie Mao and the OPA's interference in his investigation, while grappling with the moral weight of war on Ceres. His relationship with Hasini and the unresolved mystery of Julie's disappearance deepen his personal stakes in the escalating conflict."}],"summary":"The Martian Congressional Republic's secret war against the Belt has erupted into open conflict, forcing Ceres Station to navigate escalating tensions. Detective Miller grapples with his failed pursuit of Julie Mao while confronting the reality of war's impact on the station. Meanwhile, Star Helix and the OPA maneuver to control the narrative, with Holden's capture hinting at deeper conspiracies."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":21,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Julie Mao","aliases":["Juliette Andromeda Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Miller accessed her digital files, discovered personal correspondence and OPA affiliations"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seventeen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Commander and close ally"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Hosted a meal with his crew, discussed the Rocinante's systems, and initiated the transponder override."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seventeen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Superior officer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Worked on the transponder system, discussed the ship's weapons, and expressed concerns about tampering with military tech."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seventeen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Eaten hummus, joked about the ship's weapons, and expressed support for joining Fred Johnson's cause."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned from the Mao case, confronted political tensions on Ceres, and faced personal conflict over Julie's safety."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seventeen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Described the Rocinante's capabilities, mentioned the 'Mobile Assault Package,' and expressed willingness to stay with Holden's crew."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seventeen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"}],"recentEvents":"Greeted Holden's crew upon their arrival at Tycho Station."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Ex-cop from three generations in the Belt with hardened attitude toward violence","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed case assignments with Miller, hinted at systemic issues in the station's justice system."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Eros","description":"A celestial body serving as the home port of the damaged Martian freighter.","recentEvents":"The freighter, registered to Eros, sent an emergency signal requiring aid.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive space station in the asteroid belt, serving as a hub for trade and conflict between Belters and Earthlings.","recentEvents":"Detective Miller investigates the murder of Enrique Dos Santos, whose body was displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works. The incident sparks tensions between Martian authorities and Belters.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations"},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","status":"active","characters":["Fred Johnson","Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"The OPA's covert operations continue as Holden leverages Fred Johnson's network to hide the Tachi, revealing the organization's ability to manipulate Martian registries and provide sanctuary for Belters. The data cube from Lieutenant Kelly hints at deeper OPA involvement in the Donnager's destruction."},{"name":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Captain Shaddid","Martian Navy","Anderson Dawes"],"summary":"The Martian Congressional Republic officially declares war on the Belt, framing the OPA as the aggressor. Miller's investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance is sidelined as the OPA and Martian Navy escalate hostilities, with Holden's crew now in OPA custody and the station becoming a frontline zone."},{"name":"Martian Navy, OPA, and Belt Security Crisis","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal","Fred Johnson","Detective Miller"],"summary":"Holden's crew escapes the Donnager after a violent boarding action, using a stolen Martian warship (Tachi) and a forged transponder code provided by Fred Johnson. The crew now faces the challenge of evading Martian detection while dealing with casualties and the ethical weight of their actions."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","status":"active","characters":["Anderson Dawes","Captain Shaddid","Detective Miller","Juliette Mao"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism threatens to erupt into civil war as Dawes asserts control over Holden's case, revealing the OPA's covert involvement in the Donnager's destruction and their strategic manipulation of Martian-Mars tensions to protect Belt interests."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Conflict and Julie's Fate [active]","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Juliette Mao","Hasini","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"Miller confronts his failure to protect Julie Mao and the OPA's interference in his investigation, while grappling with the moral weight of war on Ceres. His relationship with Hasini and the unresolved mystery of Julie's disappearance deepen his personal stakes in the escalating conflict."}],"summary":"The Martian Congressional Republic's secret war against the Belt has erupted into open conflict, forcing Ceres Station to navigate escalating tensions. Detective Miller grapples with his failed pursuit of Julie Mao while confronting the reality of war's impact on the station. Meanwhile, Star Helix and the OPA maneuver to control the narrative, with Holden's capture hinting at deeper conspiracies."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":22,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Julie Mao","aliases":["Juliette Andromeda Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Miller accessed her digital files, discovered personal correspondence and OPA affiliations"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seventeen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Commander and close ally"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Hosted a meal with his crew, discussed the Rocinante's systems, and initiated the transponder override."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seventeen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Superior officer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Worked on the transponder system, discussed the ship's weapons, and expressed concerns about tampering with military tech."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seventeen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Eaten hummus, joked about the ship's weapons, and expressed support for joining Fred Johnson's cause."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for rape, witnessed the collapse of Ceres Station's governance, and confronted political uncertainty about the station's future."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seventeen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Described the Rocinante's capabilities, mentioned the 'Mobile Assault Package,' and expressed willingness to stay with Holden's crew."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seventeen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"}],"recentEvents":"Greeted Holden's crew upon their arrival at Tycho Station."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Eros","description":"A celestial body serving as the home port of the damaged Martian freighter.","recentEvents":"The freighter, registered to Eros, sent an emergency signal requiring aid.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Fred Johnson","Anderson Dawes"],"summary":"The OPA's covert manipulation of Martian-Belt tensions continues as Miller's investigation intersects with their strategic interests, raising questions about Holden's survival and the Donnager's destruction."},{"name":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Anderson Dawes","Shaddid"],"summary":"The collapse of Earth's governance over Ceres creates a power vacuum, forcing the OPA to potentially step in while Miller navigates political chaos and his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","status":"active","characters":["Anderson Dawes","Captain Shaddid","Detective Miller","Juliette Mao"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism threatens to erupt into civil war as Dawes asserts control over Holden's case, revealing the OPA's covert involvement in the Donnager's destruction and their strategic manipulation of Martian-Mars tensions to protect Belt interests."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Conflict and Julie's Fate","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Juliette Mao","Hasini","Naomi Nagata","Julie Mao"],"summary":"Miller confronts his failure to protect Julie Mao and the OPA's interference in his investigation, while grappling with the moral weight of war on Ceres. His relationship with Hasini and the unresolved mystery of Julie's disappearance deepen his personal stakes in the escalating conflict."}],"summary":"After the Donnager's destruction sparks Belt independence, Ceres Station grapples with political upheaval as Earth withdraws its control. Detective Miller investigates a rape case while navigating the collapse of institutional order, uncovering potential ties to larger conflicts between Mars and the Belt. The station's police force faces existential threats as power vacuums emerge."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":23,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Julie Mao","aliases":["Juliette Andromeda Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Miller accessed her digital files, discovered personal correspondence and OPA affiliations"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Commander and close ally"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated shelter at Tycho Station with Fred Johnson, confronted Fred about motives, and processed trauma from crew losses."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Superior officer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Performed karaoke, argued with Holden about rescue missions, and expressed defiance against cosmic indifference."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in bartering for services, mocked Fred's political maneuvering, and schemed for rescue missions."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for rape, witnessed the collapse of Ceres Station's governance, and confronted political uncertainty about the station's future."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in trial discussion, expressed fatalism about war, and engaged in darts competition."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seventeen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"}],"recentEvents":"Greeted Holden's crew upon their arrival at Tycho Station."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Eros","description":"A celestial body serving as the home port of the damaged Martian freighter.","recentEvents":"The freighter, registered to Eros, sent an emergency signal requiring aid.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Fred","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"Holden and his crew are offered shelter at Tycho Station by Fred, who proposes using their testimony as witnesses to a criminal trial for the Donnager's destruction. Fred's political maneuvering positions the crew as key players in shaping post-war treaties, revealing OPA's influence through covert financial ties rather than direct control."},{"name":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","status":"active","characters":["Fred","Jim Holden","Anderson Dawes","Cameron Paj"],"summary":"Fred outlines the existential threat of the Belt's asymmetric warfare against Mars, framing the trial as a way to avoid total annihilation. The OPA's indirect involvement in the conflict through political leverage is exposed, with Fred's station becoming a hub for negotiating a fragile peace."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","status":"active","characters":["Anderson Dawes","Captain Shaddid","Detective Miller","Juliette Mao"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism threatens to erupt into civil war as Dawes asserts control over Holden's case, revealing the OPA's covert involvement in the Donnager's destruction and their strategic manipulation of Martian-Mars tensions to protect Belt interests."}],"summary":"Holden and his crew are sheltered at Tycho Station, where Fred offers protection and a role in a potential trial to resolve the Belt-Mars conflict. Despite skepticism, Holden agrees to cooperate, though he remains haunted by the loss of his crew and the looming threat of war."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":24,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Julie Mao","aliases":["Juliette Andromeda Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Miller accessed her digital files, discovered personal correspondence and OPA affiliations"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Commander and close ally"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated shelter at Tycho Station with Fred Johnson, confronted Fred about motives, and processed trauma from crew losses."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Superior officer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Performed karaoke, argued with Holden about rescue missions, and expressed defiance against cosmic indifference."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in bartering for services, mocked Fred's political maneuvering, and schemed for rescue missions."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for rape, witnessed the collapse of Ceres Station's governance, and confronted political uncertainty about the station's future."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in trial discussion, expressed fatalism about war, and engaged in darts competition."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seventeen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"}],"recentEvents":"Greeted Holden's crew upon their arrival at Tycho Station."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Eros","description":"A celestial body serving as the home port of the damaged Martian freighter.","recentEvents":"The freighter, registered to Eros, sent an emergency signal requiring aid.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Fred Johnson","Anderson Dawes","Detective Miller"],"summary":"Miller's investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance intersects with OPA's covert operations, as he leverages ship logs and contacts like Havelock to track Holden. The OPA's control over Ceres and its manipulation of Martian-Belt tensions remain central to the trial's political stakes."},{"name":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","OPA","Martian Congressional Republic","Belters"],"summary":"Ceres Station's political instability and riots reflect the escalating Martian-Belt conflict. Miller's pursuit of Holden and Mao ties into the OPA's broader strategy to exploit the war for Belt interests, with Protogen and other security firms becoming new nodes in the power struggle."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","status":"active","characters":["Anderson Dawes","Captain Shaddid","Detective Miller","Juliette Mao"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism threatens to erupt into civil war as Dawes asserts control over Holden's case, revealing the OPA's covert involvement in the Donnager's destruction and their strategic manipulation of Martian-Mars tensions to protect Belt interests."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Julie Mao","Jim Holden"],"summary":"Miller's quest to find Holden and Mao becomes a standalone arc as he navigates Ceres' chaos, uses his detective skills to track the Rocinante, and confronts the personal stakes of his job loss. His determination to pursue the case despite systemic barriers drives this thread."}],"summary":"Miller navigates Ceres Station's political chaos, tracking leads on Julie Mao while grappling with his diminished status. Meanwhile, the Belt's escalating conflict intensifies as OPA-aligned prospectors on Triton leak Martian military data, threatening to ignite a full-scale war between Earth, Mars, and the outer planets."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":25,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Julie Mao","aliases":["Juliette Andromeda Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Miller accessed her digital files, discovered personal correspondence and OPA affiliations"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Commander and close ally"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Proposed a plan to take the Rocinante on a mission to Eros, discussed the data cube with Naomi, and negotiated with Fred."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Superior officer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to the Eros mission, discussed the data cube with Holden, and expressed appreciation for his leadership."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Expressed frustration with station life, participated in the Eros mission planning, and gambled at card tables."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for rape, witnessed the collapse of Ceres Station's governance, and confronted political uncertainty about the station's future."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to the Eros mission, discussed vengeance with Holden, and gambled at card tables."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated the use of the Rocinante for an Eros mission, revealed the fictional Lionel Polanski, and discussed the data cube."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Identified as the nonexistent owner of the Scopuli, targeted for retrieval by Fred Johnson's agents."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Eros","description":"A celestial body serving as the home port of the damaged Martian freighter.","recentEvents":"The freighter, registered to Eros, sent an emergency signal requiring aid.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Fred Johnson","Anderson Dawes","Detective Miller"],"summary":"Miller's investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance intersects with OPA's covert operations, as he leverages ship logs and contacts like Havelock to track Holden. The OPA's control over Ceres and its manipulation of Martian-Belt tensions remain central to the trial's political stakes."},{"name":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","OPA","Martian Congressional Republic","Belters"],"summary":"Ceres Station's political instability and riots reflect the escalating Martian-Belt conflict. Miller's pursuit of Holden and Mao ties into the OPA's broader strategy to exploit the war for Belt interests, with Protogen and other security firms becoming new nodes in the power struggle."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","status":"active","characters":["Anderson Dawes","Captain Shaddid","Detective Miller","Juliette Mao"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism threatens to erupt into civil war as Dawes asserts control over Holden's case, revealing the OPA's covert involvement in the Donnager's destruction and their strategic manipulation of Martian-Mars tensions to protect Belt interests."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Julie Mao","Jim Holden"],"summary":"Miller's quest to find Holden and Mao becomes a standalone arc as he navigates Ceres' chaos, uses his detective skills to track the Rocinante, and confronts the personal stakes of his job loss. His determination to pursue the case despite systemic barriers drives this thread."}],"summary":"Miller navigates Ceres Station's political chaos, tracking leads on Julie Mao while grappling with his diminished status. Meanwhile, the Belt's escalating conflict intensifies as OPA-aligned prospectors on Triton leak Martian military data, threatening to ignite a full-scale war between Earth, Mars, and the outer planets."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":26,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Julie Mao","aliases":["Juliette Andromeda Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Miller accessed her digital files, discovered personal correspondence and OPA affiliations"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Commander and close ally"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Proposed a plan to take the Rocinante on a mission to Eros, discussed the data cube with Naomi, and negotiated with Fred."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Superior officer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to the Eros mission, discussed the data cube with Holden, and expressed appreciation for his leadership."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Expressed frustration with station life, participated in the Eros mission planning, and gambled at card tables."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Former colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Discussing the CPM security contract, searching for Julie Mao, reflecting on leaving Ceres"},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to the Eros mission, discussed vengeance with Holden, and gambled at card tables."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated the use of the Rocinante for an Eros mission, revealed the fictional Lionel Polanski, and discussed the data cube."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Identified as the nonexistent owner of the Scopuli, targeted for retrieval by Fred Johnson's agents."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A Ceres security officer working for the CPM contract","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Former colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Discussing the CPM security contract and Julie Mao's case with Miller"}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Eros","description":"A celestial body serving as the home port of the damaged Martian freighter.","recentEvents":"The freighter, registered to Eros, sent an emergency signal requiring aid.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy"},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Inspector Sematimba","Julie Mao","Anderson Dawes"],"summary":"Miller's investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance intersects with OPA's covert operations, as he seeks information from Sematimba about the war's escalation and Ceres' secession, revealing deeper ties to OPA's strategic manipulation of Martian-Belt tensions."},{"name":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Inspector Sematimba","OPA","CPM"],"summary":"The war between Mars and the Belt escalates, with Ceres' secession and Protogen's exit destabilizing Eros. Miller's pursuit of Julie Mao connects to OPA's broader control over security contracts and its exploitation of Belt interests through new corporations like CPM."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","status":"active","characters":["Anderson Dawes","Captain Shaddid","Detective Miller","Juliette Mao"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism threatens to erupt into civil war as Dawes asserts control over Holden's case, revealing the OPA's covert involvement in the Donnager's destruction and their strategic manipulation of Martian-Mars tensions to protect Belt interests."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Julie Mao","Inspector Sematimba"],"summary":"Miller continues his search for Julie Mao, navigating Eros' lawless environment and leveraging his detective skills to track the Rocinante, while confronting the personal stakes of his job loss and systemic barriers."}],"summary":"Miller is on Eros, investigating Julie Mao's case while reflecting on his past as a Ceres cop. He meets Inspector Sematimba and learns about the station's political tensions and new security contract, while waiting for the Rocinante's arrival."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":27,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Julie Mao","aliases":["Juliette Andromeda Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Miller accessed her digital files, discovered personal correspondence and OPA affiliations"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Commander and close ally"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Led a confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse, survived a gunfight with armed assailants."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Superior officer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Survived a gunfight at Lionel Polanski's flophouse, instructed Holden to check on Polanski."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in a gunfight at Lionel Polanski's flophouse, engaged in combat with armed assailants."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"