:"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the t