ons between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A Ceres security officer working for the CPM contract","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Former colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Discussing the CPM security contract and Julie Mao's case with Miller"},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Strategic Manipulation of Martian-Belt Tensions","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Eros","arc":"OPA's Strategic Manipulation of Martian-Belt Tensions","description":"A celestial body serving as the home port of the damaged Martian freighter.","recentEvents":"The freighter, registered to Eros, sent an emergency signal requiring aid.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Strategic Manipulation of Martian-Belt Tensions","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Strategic Manipulation of Martian-Belt Tensions","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Strategic Manipulation of Martian-Belt Tensions","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton","Anderson Dawes","Inspector Sematimba","OPA","CPM"],"summary":"The war between Mars and the Belt escalates, with Ceres' secession and Protogen's exit destabilizing Eros. Miller's pursuit of Julie Mao connects to OPA's broader control over security contracts and its exploitation of Belt interests through new corporations like CPM."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","status":"active","characters":["Anderson Dawes","Captain Shaddid","Detective Miller","Juliette Mao"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism threatens to erupt into civil war as Dawes asserts control over Holden's case, revealing the OPA's covert involvement in the Donnager's destruction and their strategic manipulation of Martian-Mars tensions to protect Belt interests."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton"],"summary":"Miller's pursuit of Julie Mao intensifies as he navigates Eros' dangers, now directly clashing with armed factions linked to OPA's operations and the Martian-Belt war."}],"summary":"Holden and his crew are on Eros, investigating Lionel Polanski. They encounter a dangerous situation at a flophouse, leading to a gunfight with armed individuals. Holden and his team manage to survive the confrontation, though several are injured."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":28,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Target of search"}],"recentEvents":"Discovered dead in shower stall with severe biological modifications"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Commander and close ally"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Survived ambush, discussed search for Scopuli crew member"},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Superior officer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Survived ambush, witnessed discovery of Juliette Mao's body"},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Group member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Kicked in door to search room, revealed leg injury"},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Survived a firefight, discovered Juliette Mao's body, coordinated with police"},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Survived a gunfight at Lionel Polanski's flophouse, targeted by an armed assailant."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated the use of the Rocinante for an Eros mission, revealed the fictional Lionel Polanski, and discussed the data cube."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A Ceres security officer working for the CPM contract","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with police, assessed Juliette Mao's death scene"},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Covert Operations and Strategic Manipulation","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Covert Operations and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros flophouse","aliases":["Eros"],"arc":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","description":"A communal living space on Eros for off-world residents, known for its cramped and utilitarian design.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden's group are ambushed here, leading to a confrontation and the discovery of Juliette Mao's corpse in a room.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Adjacent space station in the Belt"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Covert Operations and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Jim Holden","Juliette Mao","Anderson Dawes","Amos Burton"],"summary":"Miller discovers Juliette Mao's corpse in a flophouse, revealing OPA's involvement in her death through experimental procedures. The OPA's covert manipulation of Martian-Belt tensions now directly ties to their control over Holden's survival and the Donnager's destruction."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","status":"active","characters":["Anderson Dawes","Captain Shaddid","Detective Miller","Juliette Mao"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism threatens to erupt into civil war as Dawes asserts control over Holden's case, revealing the OPA's covert involvement in the Donnager's destruction and their strategic manipulation of Martian-Mars tensions to protect Belt interests."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton"],"summary":"Miller confronts Holden and his crew after a deadly ambush, realizing the attack was a setup linked to OPA's operations. The investigation now centers on uncovering the full scope of OPA's experiments and their connection to Mao's death."}],"summary":"Miller and Holden's group are at the Eros flophouse after an ambush, where they discover Juliette Andromeda Mao's corpse in a room. The police arrive, and Miller reveals the attack was a setup, implicating Holden's return and the Scopuli's connection. The situation escalates as the group faces potential dangers."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":29,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Target of search"}],"recentEvents":"Discovered dead in shower stall with severe biological modifications"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Allies in the investigation"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Accompanied by Miller during the investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Survived a gunfight, discussed Julie Mao's case, and planned to leave Eros."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Allies in the investigation"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Handled Julie Mao's terminal, discussed the Phoebe bug, and analyzed her notes."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Argued with Miller about promises, participated in the gunfight, and questioned the mission's risks."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Accompanied Holden during the investigation"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Collaborated on the investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Investigated Julie Mao's death, faced a gunfight, and discussed his past with Holden."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Washed up after being sick, assisted in analyzing the terminal, and contributed to the group's discussions."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated the use of the Rocinante for an Eros mission, revealed the fictional Lionel Polanski, and discussed the data cube."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A Ceres security officer working for the CPM contract","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with police, assessed Juliette Mao's death scene"},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Covert Operations and Strategic Manipulation","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"Martian-Belt Conflict and OPA's Role","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Covert Operations and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros flophouse","aliases":["Eros"],"arc":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","description":"A communal living space on Eros for off-world residents, known for its cramped and utilitarian design.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden's group are ambushed here, leading to a confrontation and the discovery of Juliette Mao's corpse in a room.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Adjacent space station in the Belt"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112"],"description":"A designated rock in the asteroid belt with potential hidden significance.","recentEvents":"Holden and crew plan to investigate BA834024112 after discovering Julie's terminal notes linking it to her shuttle's origin.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"}],"arc":"OPA's Covert Operations and Strategic Manipulation"}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Covert Operations and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"Miller's investigation into Juliette Mao's death reveals OPA's experimental bioweapon (Phoebe bug) and ties it to BA834024112, a potential hidden ship. Holden's crew now seeks to uncover OPA's role in the bioweapon's creation and its connection to the Martian-Belt conflict."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War [active]","status":"active","characters":["Anderson Dawes","Captain Shaddid","Detective Miller","Juliette Mao"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism threatens to erupt into civil war as Dawes asserts control over Holden's case, revealing the OPA's covert involvement in the Donnager's destruction and their strategic manipulation of Martian-Mars tensions to protect Belt interests."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"Miller's grief over Juliette's death evolves into a determination to expose her killers, now linked to OPA's bioweapon. His survival hinges on balancing his personal quest with the crew's escape from Eros."}],"summary":"Holden's group remains on Eros after a chaotic gunfight in the hotel lobby, where they uncover Julie's terminal detailing a Phoebe bug infection and a mysterious rock designation BA834024112. They plan to investigate the rock's location in the asteroid belt while navigating threats from unknown attackers and the bioweapon's potential spread. Miller's unresolved connection to Julie complicates their mission, as does the risk of contamination from the Phoebe bug."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":30,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Target of search"}],"recentEvents":"Discovered dead in shower stall with severe biological modifications"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Allies in the investigation"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Accompanied by Miller during the investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated with Detective Miller for ship access, received a warning about a bioweapon leak, and fled an explosion at Eros Station."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Allies in the investigation"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed extortion risks with Miller, analyzed the bioweapon threat, and evacuated Eros Station during an explosion."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in negotiations with Miller, discussed the bioweapon threat, and evacuated Eros Station during an explosion."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Accompanied Holden during the investigation"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Collaborated on the investigation"},{"character":"Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted police"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated with Holden for ship access, received a warning about a bioweapon leak, and fled an explosion at Eros Station."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in negotiations with Miller, discussed the bioweapon threat, and evacuated Eros Station during an explosion."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated the use of the Rocinante for an Eros mission, revealed the fictional Lionel Polanski, and discussed the data cube."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros flophouse","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station"],"arc":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","description":"A space station in the Belt serving as a major hub for trade and transit between Ceres, Ganymede, and other outer stations.","recentEvents":"The station entered emergency lockdown after an explosion triggered a radiological safety protocol, forcing evacuations to the casino level. A mole in Tycho Station leaked information about Holden's presence, escalating tensions over a bioweapon's potential release.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Adjacent space station in the Belt"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Mole activity originated here"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A designated rock in the asteroid belt with potential hidden significance.","recentEvents":"Holden and crew plan to investigate BA834024112 after discovering Julie's terminal notes linking it to her shuttle's origin.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter"],"description":"A designated safety zone within Eros Station for radiation containment during emergencies.","recentEvents":"Crowds were directed here for shelter after the explosion, though its effectiveness against a potential bioweapon remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Sub-level within the station"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"Miller's investigation into Juliette Mao's death reveals OPA's experimental bioweapon (Phoebe bug) and ties it to BA834024112, a potential hidden ship. Holden's crew now seeks to uncover OPA's role in the bioweapon's creation and its connection to the Martian-Belt conflict."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","status":"active","characters":["Anderson Dawes","Captain Shaddid","Detective Miller","Juliette Mao","OPA Man","Shed Garvey","Captain McDowell"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism threatens to erupt into civil war as Dawes asserts control over Holden's case, revealing the OPA's covert involvement in the Donnager's destruction and their strategic manipulation of Martian-Mars tensions to protect Belt interests."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Jim Holden","Amos Burton"],"summary":"Miller's pursuit of Julie Mao's killers intersects with OPA's bioweapon plot, forcing him to navigate Eros' chaos while evading CPM security forces and uncovering OPA's role in the bioweapon's deployment."},{"name":"OPA's Covert Operations and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Anderson Dawes","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"Miller uncovers OPA's bioweapon shipment and links it to Stage Three, realizing the attack on Eros is a diversion to move the infected sample. Holden's crew now faces the threat of the bioweapon's spread."}],"summary":"Eros Station is locked down after an explosion triggers a radiological emergency, with Holden and his crew racing to secure their ship while a bioweapon's threat looms. A mole's leak reveals their location, forcing a chaotic evacuation to the casino level as tensions escalate over Julie Mao's missing body and the sample's potential use in a larger attack."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":31,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Target of search"}],"recentEvents":"Discovered dead in shower stall with severe biological modifications"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Allies in the investigation"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Accompanied by Miller during the investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Planned to infiltrate a radiation shelter, got exposed to radioactive gas, and shot a guard."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Allies in the investigation"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Holden about the dangers of the shelter, then ordered to stay behind."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Disabled a card reader to access the maintenance corridor."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Accompanied Holden during the investigation"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Collaborated on the investigation"},{"character":"Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted police"}],"recentEvents":"Planned the escape, got exposed to radioactive gas, and shot a guard."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Naomi's argument about the mobsters' motives."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated the use of the Rocinante for an Eros mission, revealed the fictional Lionel Polanski, and discussed the data cube."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."},{"name":"Guard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A fake riot cop leading civilians to a radiation shelter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot by Miller and Holden after being ordered to open a sealed shelter."},{"name":"Gabby Smalls","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A mobster and police riot gear supervisor on Ceres, leading civilians to shelters.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as a key figure in the Ceres protection racket."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros flophouse","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station"],"arc":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","description":"A space station in the Belt serving as a major hub for trade and transit between Ceres, Ganymede, and other outer stations.","recentEvents":"The station entered emergency lockdown after an explosion triggered a radiological safety protocol, forcing evacuations to the casino level. A mole in Tycho Station leaked information about Holden's presence, escalating tensions over a bioweapon's potential release.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Adjacent space station in the Belt"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Mole activity originated here"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A designated rock in the asteroid belt with potential hidden significance.","recentEvents":"Holden and crew plan to investigate BA834024112 after discovering Julie's terminal notes linking it to her shuttle's origin.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter"],"description":"A designated safety zone within Eros Station for radiation containment during emergencies.","recentEvents":"Crowds were directed here for shelter after the explosion, though its effectiveness against a potential bioweapon remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Sub-level within the station"}]},{"name":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","aliases":["Maintenance Tunnel"],"description":"A dimly lit service passage carved by early Belters, housing critical power lines and running through the first Belt colony's infrastructure.","recentEvents":"Holden, Naomi, and others hide here while evading Ceres mobsters, using a hacked card reader to bypass security. They later infiltrate a radiation shelter disguised as a safe zone.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's utility infrastructure"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Adjacent to casino areas but avoided by crowds"}],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation"},{"name":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","aliases":["Radiation Lockdown Zones"],"description":"Sealed-off sections of Eros Station purportedly designed to protect citizens from radiation, but secretly used as containment areas for lethal gas and biological agents.","recentEvents":"Holden and Miller are exposed to a toxic gas and radiation after infiltrating the shelter, discovering it was a trap orchestrated by the mobsters.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Designated emergency lockdown zones"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via transit corridors"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"Miller's investigation into Juliette Mao's death reveals OPA's experimental bioweapon (Phoebe bug) and ties it to BA834024112, a potential hidden ship. Holden's crew now seeks to uncover OPA's role in the bioweapon's creation and its connection to the Martian-Belt conflict."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","status":"dormant","characters":["Anderson Dawes","OPA Man","Cameron Paj"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism and strategic manipulation of Belt-Mars tensions are paused as the focus shifts to Eros' immediate bioweapon crisis, though underlying political conflicts remain unresolved."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"Miller uncovers OPA's bioweapon deployment and its connection to Stage Three, while Holden's crew navigates Eros' chaos to reach the ship, facing lethal gas and OPA's enforcers."},{"name":"OPA's Strategic Manipulation and Bioweapon Deployment","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton"],"summary":"Holden and Miller discover the radiation shelters are gas-filled, revealing OPA's use of the Phoebe bug to control populations. The bioweapon's spread and OPA's covert operations to manipulate Belt-Mars tensions remain active threats."}],"summary":"Holden and his allies evade Ceres mobsters by hiding in Eros Station's maintenance corridors, but their attempt to investigate the radiation shelters leads to a deadly exposure. With the station under lockdown and radiation levels rising, they must flee to the Roci before their injuries become fatal."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":32,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Target of search"}],"recentEvents":"Discovered dead in shower stall with severe biological modifications"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Allies in the investigation"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Accompanied by Miller during the investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Evaded guards on Eros, coordinated with Miller to bypass security, and returned to the hideout."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Allies in the investigation"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Holden about the dangers of the shelter, then ordered to stay behind."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Disabled a card reader to access the maintenance corridor."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Died instantly from a gauss round fired during the Donnager's engagement with the Belt ships."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Accompanied Holden during the investigation"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Collaborated on the investigation"},{"character":"Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted police"}],"recentEvents":"Confronted guards on Eros, killed Mikey Ko, and navigated radiation-infested corridors to reach the hideout."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Naomi's argument about the mobsters' motives."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated the use of the Rocinante for an Eros mission, revealed the fictional Lionel Polanski, and discussed the data cube."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."},{"name":"Guard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A fake riot cop leading civilians to a radiation shelter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot by Miller and Holden after being ordered to open a sealed shelter."},{"name":"Gabby Smalls","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A mobster and police riot gear supervisor on Ceres, leading civilians to shelters.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as a key figure in the Ceres protection racket."},{"name":"Mikey Ko","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A guard who mistook Miller and Holden for Protogen installers, leading to his death at Miller's hands.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's lethal action"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Witness to Miller's confrontation"}],"recentEvents":"Was killed by Miller after revealing details about Protogen's operations on Eros."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros flophouse","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A massive asteroid station with multiple levels, serving as a hub for illegal activities and a key location for the story's events.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden navigate Eros Station's corridors to avoid guards, using the maintenance corridor and radiation shelters. They encounter Mikey Ko and learn about Protogen's operations.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Adjacent space station in the Belt"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Mole activity originated here"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent to the maintenance corridors"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Part of the lockdown area"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A designated rock in the asteroid belt with potential hidden significance.","recentEvents":"Holden and crew plan to investigate BA834024112 after discovering Julie's terminal notes linking it to her shuttle's origin.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter","Casino Area"],"description":"A restricted zone on Eros Station where the population is funneled during lockdowns, serving as a central gathering point.","recentEvents":"The level is under lockdown, with guards enforcing movement toward shelters. Miller and Holden use this as a strategic point to regroup.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's structure"}]},{"name":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","aliases":["Maintenance Tunnel","Maintenance Shaft"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A dimly lit service passage carved by early Belters, housing critical power lines and running through the first Belt colony's infrastructure.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden use this corridor to evade guards and reach the hideout. Ko's body is carried through here.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's utility infrastructure"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Adjacent to casino areas but avoided by crowds"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent"}]},{"name":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","aliases":["Radiation Lockdown Zones","Radiation Incubators"],"description":"Sealed-off sections of Eros Station purportedly designed to protect citizens from radiation, but secretly used as containment areas for lethal gas and biological agents.","recentEvents":"The shelters were emptied, leaving only Holden and Miller's footsteps. Ko's body is left here after being shot.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Designated emergency lockdown zones"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via transit corridors"},{"location":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","relationship":"Located nearby"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"Miller's investigation into Juliette Mao's death reveals OPA's experimental bioweapon (Phoebe bug) and ties it to BA834024112, a potential hidden ship. Holden's crew now seeks to uncover OPA's role in the bioweapon's creation and its connection to the Martian-Belt conflict."},{"name":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","status":"dormant","characters":["Anderson Dawes","OPA Man","Cameron Paj"],"summary":"The OPA's internal schism and strategic manipulation of Belt-Mars tensions are paused as the focus shifts to Eros' immediate bioweapon crisis, though underlying political conflicts remain unresolved."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"Miller uncovers OPA's bioweapon deployment and its connection to Stage Three, while Holden's crew navigates Eros' chaos to reach the ship, facing lethal gas and OPA's enforcers."},{"name":"OPA's Strategic Manipulation and Bioweapon Deployment","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton"],"summary":"Holden and Miller discover the radiation shelters are gas-filled, revealing OPA's use of the Phoebe bug to control populations. The bioweapon's spread and OPA's covert operations to manipulate Belt-Mars tensions remain active threats."}],"summary":"Miller and Holden navigate Eros Station's hazardous corridors to evade guards and reach Naomi's hideout, uncovering Protogen's secret operations. Miller grapples with his descent into violence, while radiation sickness looms as a threat. The hideout, once a refuge, is now empty, leaving them stranded with no clear path forward."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":33,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Target of search"}],"recentEvents":"Discovered dead in shower stall with severe biological modifications"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Ex-lover and former crewmate"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Accompanied by Miller during the investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Experienced despair over Naomi's departure, engaged in a shootout with mafia thugs, and rescued a dead child."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Ex-lover and former crewmate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Left Holden on Eros station, prompting his emotional breakdown and subsequent actions."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Disabled a card reader to access the maintenance corridor."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned by Holden as someone he wished was still alive."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Accompanied Holden during the investigation"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Collaborated on the investigation"},{"character":"Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted police"}],"recentEvents":"Planned with Holden to reach his ship, witnessed a violent mob incident, and assisted in rescuing a child."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Naomi's argument about the mobsters' motives."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated the use of the Rocinante for an Eros mission, revealed the fictional Lionel Polanski, and discussed the data cube."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."},{"name":"Guard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A fake riot cop leading civilians to a radiation shelter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nudged by Miller after the shootout."},{"name":"Gabby Smalls","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A mobster and police riot gear supervisor on Ceres, leading civilians to shelters.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as a key figure in the Ceres protection racket."},{"name":"Mikey Ko","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A guard who mistook Miller and Holden for Protogen installers, leading to his death at Miller's hands.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's lethal action"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Witness to Miller's confrontation"}],"recentEvents":"Was killed by Miller after revealing details about Protogen's operations on Eros."},{"name":"Mafia Thug","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A violent enforcer killed by Holden during a mob incident.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Holden after firing on civilians."},{"name":"Child Victim","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A thirteen-year-old boy killed by the mafia thug during the chaos on Eros station.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died from a gunshot wound to the chest, rescued by Holden."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros flophouse","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A massive asteroid station with multiple levels, serving as a hub for illegal activities and a key location for the story's events.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden navigate Eros Station's corridors to avoid guards, using the maintenance corridor and radiation shelters. They encounter Mikey Ko and learn about Protogen's operations.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Adjacent space station in the Belt"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Mole activity originated here"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent to the maintenance corridors"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Part of the lockdown area"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A designated rock in the asteroid belt with potential hidden significance.","recentEvents":"Holden and crew plan to investigate BA834024112 after discovering Julie's terminal notes linking it to her shuttle's origin.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter","Casino Area"],"description":"A restricted zone on Eros Station where the population is funneled during lockdowns, serving as a central gathering point.","recentEvents":"The level is under lockdown, with guards enforcing movement toward shelters. Miller and Holden use this as a strategic point to regroup.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's structure"}]},{"name":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","aliases":["Maintenance Tunnel","Maintenance Shaft"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A dimly lit service passage carved by early Belters, housing critical power lines and running through the first Belt colony's infrastructure.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden use this corridor to evade guards and reach the hideout. Ko's body is carried through here.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's utility infrastructure"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Adjacent to casino areas but avoided by crowds"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent"}]},{"name":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","aliases":["Radiation Lockdown Zones","Radiation Incubators"],"description":"Sealed-off sections of Eros Station purportedly designed to protect citizens from radiation, but secretly used as containment areas for lethal gas and biological agents.","recentEvents":"The shelters were emptied, leaving only Holden and Miller's footsteps. Ko's body is left here after being shot.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Designated emergency lockdown zones"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via transit corridors"},{"location":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","relationship":"Located nearby"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton"],"summary":"Holden and Miller confront OPA's lethal bioweapon (Phoebe bug) in Eros' radiation shelters, now revealed as gas-filled containment zones. Holden's crew faces imminent death from the bioweapon's effects while navigating mafia violence and OPA enforcers."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Jim Holden"],"summary":"Miller's pursuit of OPA's bioweapon leads to a deadly confrontation with mafia thugs, resulting in a child's death. Holden's desperation to reach their ship underscores the stakes of surviving OPA's biological warfare."},{"name":"OPA's Strategic Manipulation and Bioweapon Deployment","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"The bioweapon's spread and OPA's use of radiation shelters as gas containment facilities escalate, with Holden's crew racing to reach their ship while evading OPA's enforcers and the toxic environment."}],"summary":"Miller and Holden navigate Eros Station's hazardous corridors to evade guards and reach Naomi's hideout, uncovering Protogen's secret operations. Miller grapples with his descent into violence, while radiation sickness looms as a threat. The hideout, once a refuge, is now empty, leaving them stranded with no clear path forward."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":34,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Target of search"}],"recentEvents":"Discovered dead in shower stall with severe biological modifications"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Ex-lover and former crewmate"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Accompanied by Miller during the investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in dialogue with Miller about the zombie threat, expressed nausea, and planned to follow mercenaries"},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Ex-lover and former crewmate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Left Holden on Eros station, prompting his emotional breakdown and subsequent actions."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Disabled a card reader to access the maintenance corridor."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned by Holden as someone he wished was still alive."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Partner in investigating the station's crisis"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Collaborated on the investigation"},{"character":"Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted police"}],"recentEvents":"Contemplated his mortality, discussed the zombie outbreak, and coordinated with Holden to pursue mercenaries"},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Naomi's argument about the mobsters' motives."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated the use of the Rocinante for an Eros mission, revealed the fictional Lionel Polanski, and discussed the data cube."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."},{"name":"Guard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A fake riot cop leading civilians to a radiation shelter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nudged by Miller after the shootout."},{"name":"Gabby Smalls","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A mobster and police riot gear supervisor on Ceres, leading civilians to shelters.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as a key figure in the Ceres protection racket."},{"name":"Mikey Ko","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A guard who mistook Miller and Holden for Protogen installers, leading to his death at Miller's hands.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's lethal action"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Witness to Miller's confrontation"}],"recentEvents":"Was killed by Miller after revealing details about Protogen's operations on Eros."},{"name":"Mafia Thug","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A violent enforcer killed by Holden during a mob incident.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Holden after firing on civilians."},{"name":"Child Victim","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A thirteen-year-old boy killed by the mafia thug during the chaos on Eros station.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died from a gunshot wound to the chest, rescued by Holden."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros flophouse","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A massive asteroid station with multiple levels, serving as a hub for illegal activities and a key location for the story's events.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden navigate Eros Station's corridors to avoid guards, using the maintenance corridor and radiation shelters. They encounter Mikey Ko and learn about Protogen's operations.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Adjacent space station in the Belt"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Mole activity originated here"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent to the maintenance corridors"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Part of the lockdown area"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A designated rock in the asteroid belt with potential hidden significance.","recentEvents":"Holden and crew plan to investigate BA834024112 after discovering Julie's terminal notes linking it to her shuttle's origin.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter","Casino Area"],"description":"A restricted zone on Eros Station where the population is funneled during lockdowns, serving as a central gathering point.","recentEvents":"The level is under lockdown, with guards enforcing movement toward shelters. Miller and Holden use this as a strategic point to regroup.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's structure"}]},{"name":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","aliases":["Maintenance Tunnel","Maintenance Shaft"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A dimly lit service passage carved by early Belters, housing critical power lines and running through the first Belt colony's infrastructure.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden use this corridor to evade guards and reach the hideout. Ko's body is carried through here.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's utility infrastructure"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Adjacent to casino areas but avoided by crowds"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent"}]},{"name":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","aliases":["Radiation Lockdown Zones","Radiation Incubators"],"description":"Sealed-off sections of Eros Station purportedly designed to protect citizens from radiation, but secretly used as containment areas for lethal gas and biological agents.","recentEvents":"The shelters were emptied, leaving only Holden and Miller's footsteps. Ko's body is left here after being shot.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Designated emergency lockdown zones"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via transit corridors"},{"location":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","relationship":"Located nearby"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton"],"summary":"The bioweapon's lethal effects manifest as zombie-like outbreaks on Eros, revealing OPA's use of radiation shelters as containment zones. Miller theorizes the experiment's purpose is to observe the organism's behavior in controlled environments, while Holden and his crew navigate the chaos to reach their ship."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Jim Holden"],"summary":"Miller confronts his mortality and unresolved grief over Juliette Mao's death while investigating OPA's bioweapon. His internal struggle with acceptance intersects with the external threat of the bioweapon's spread, forcing him to balance survival with moral reckoning."},{"name":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"Holden's crew races to escape Eros Station as OPA's bioweapon escalates. The mercenaries' coordinated withdrawal suggests a larger strategy, prompting Holden to pursue the path toward the port while managing his own physical deterioration from the toxic environment."}],"summary":"Miller and Holden navigate Eros Station's hazardous corridors to evade guards and reach Naomi's hideout, uncovering Protogen's secret operations. Miller grapples with his descent into violence, while radiation sickness looms as a threat. The hideout, once a refuge, is now empty, leaving them stranded with no clear path forward."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":35,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Target of search"}],"recentEvents":"Discovered dead in shower stall with severe biological modifications"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Ex-lover and former crewmate"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Accompanied by Miller during the investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Injured during a corridor firefight, forced to wear stolen armor, and narrowly escaped death in the elevator."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"Chief engineer of the Canterbury. A Belter with a sharp demeanor and a reputation for technical expertise.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Ex-lover and former crewmate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Left Holden on Eros station, prompting his emotional breakdown and subsequent actions."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station airlock","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Stood guard at the airlock while Holden and Miller limped toward the elevator."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned by Holden as someone he wished was still alive."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"OPA contact"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Partner in investigating the station's crisis"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Collaborated on the investigation"},{"character":"Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted police"}],"recentEvents":"Injured during a corridor firefight, lost his left arm, and collapsed in the elevator."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Reassigned Miller from the Mao case, emphasized Star Helix's neutrality in Martian conflicts."},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station maintenance corridor","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Naomi's argument about the mobsters' motives."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock","aliases":["Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to take sick leave to avoid potential conflict, supporting Miller's decision to continue the investigation despite OPA warnings."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated the use of the Rocinante for an Eros mission, revealed the fictional Lionel Polanski, and discussed the data cube."},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."},{"name":"Guard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A fake riot cop leading civilians to a radiation shelter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nudged by Miller after the shootout."},{"name":"Gabby Smalls","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A mobster and police riot gear supervisor on Ceres, leading civilians to shelters.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as a key figure in the Ceres protection racket."},{"name":"Mikey Ko","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A guard who mistook Miller and Holden for Protogen installers, leading to his death at Miller's hands.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's lethal action"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Witness to Miller's confrontation"}],"recentEvents":"Was killed by Miller after revealing details about Protogen's operations on Eros."},{"name":"Mafia Thug","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A violent enforcer killed by Holden during a mob incident.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Holden after firing on civilians."},{"name":"Child Victim","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A thirteen-year-old boy killed by the mafia thug during the chaos on Eros station.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died from a gunshot wound to the chest, rescued by Holden."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"OPA's Dual Role and Covert Operations","description":"A large, heavily modified transport ship serving as the primary setting for the events.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao was captured and held in a storage locker aboard the ship. She later escapes and explores the ship's decks, discovering the reactor's corrupted state.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The government of Ceres collapsed as Earth withdrew its oversight, leading to the formation of a provisional government. Detective Miller arrested Immanuel Corvus Dowd for a rape case, and the station's police force faced uncertainty about their authority.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Political Manipulation and Trial Strategy","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's last known employment and her apartment's network partition were linked to this station.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Hosted the docking of the Knight, conducted interrogations of Holden's crew, and engaged in a close-quarters battle with Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros flophouse","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A massive asteroid station with multiple levels, serving as a hub for illegal activities and a key location for the story's events.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden navigate Eros Station's corridors to avoid guards, using the maintenance corridor and radiation shelters. They encounter Mikey Ko and learn about Protogen's operations.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Adjacent space station in the Belt"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Mole activity originated here"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent to the maintenance corridors"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Part of the lockdown area"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A designated rock in the asteroid belt with potential hidden significance.","recentEvents":"Holden and crew plan to investigate BA834024112 after discovering Julie's terminal notes linking it to her shuttle's origin.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter","Casino Area"],"description":"A restricted zone on Eros Station where the population is funneled during lockdowns, serving as a central gathering point.","recentEvents":"The level is under lockdown, with guards enforcing movement toward shelters. Miller and Holden use this as a strategic point to regroup.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's structure"}]},{"name":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","aliases":["Maintenance Tunnel","Maintenance Shaft"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A dimly lit service passage carved by early Belters, housing critical power lines and running through the first Belt colony's infrastructure.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden use this corridor to evade guards and reach the hideout. Ko's body is carried through here.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's utility infrastructure"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Adjacent to casino areas but avoided by crowds"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent"}]},{"name":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","aliases":["Radiation Lockdown Zones","Radiation Incubators"],"description":"Sealed-off sections of Eros Station purportedly designed to protect citizens from radiation, but secretly used as containment areas for lethal gas and biological agents.","recentEvents":"The shelters were emptied, leaving only Holden and Miller's footsteps. Ko's body is left here after being shot.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Designated emergency lockdown zones"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via transit corridors"},{"location":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","relationship":"Located nearby"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton"],"summary":"The bioweapon's zombie outbreaks and OPA's radiation shelter containment strategies intensify as Holden and Miller navigate Eros Station's chaos. Miller theorizes the bioweapon's purpose as a controlled experiment gone awry, while Holden's crew faces escalating threats from both OPA and mercenary factions."},{"name":"Miller's Personal Investigation and Survival","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Jim Holden"],"summary":"Miller confronts his unresolved grief over Juliette Mao while balancing survival against the bioweapon's spread. His moral reckoning peaks when he hesitates to shoot an innocent victim, forcing him to reconcile his duty with his humanity amid escalating violence."},{"name":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Amos Burton","Naomi Nagata","Detective Miller"],"summary":"Holden's crew races toward the ship's lift, but the corridor becomes a war zone as mercenary factions clash. Holden and Miller are gravely injured, forcing them to rely on scavenged armor for survival while navigating lethal crossfire and the bioweapon's toxic environment."}],"summary":"Holden and Miller navigate Eros Station's corridors during a chaotic firefight between mercenary factions, narrowly escaping gunfire and casualties. They reach the airlock to board the Rocinante, but Holden is severely injured, forcing them to rely on Amos for rescue. The chapter highlights the escalating conflict and the crew's desperate struggle to survive."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":36,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Target of search"}],"recentEvents":"Discovered dead in shower stall with severe biological modifications"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden","aliases":["James Holden","Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Holden's ship sick bay","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Commander and romantic interest"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Accompanied by Miller during the investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Recovered from injuries, confronted Naomi about his feelings, and discussed the destruction of Eros and his guilt over past actions."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Holden's ship sick bay","description":"Medical officer who tends to Miller and Holden. Engages in a tense conversation with Holden about his feelings for her.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and romantic interest"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Provided medical care to Miller and Holden, confronted Holden about his feelings, and discussed the aftermath of Eros."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-One: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station airlock","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"}],"recentEvents":"Stood guard at the airlock while Holden and Miller limped toward the elevator."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned by Holden as someone he wished was still alive."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Holden's ship sick bay","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":