an, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."},{"name":"Guard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A fake riot cop leading civilians to a radiation shelter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nudged by Miller after the shootout."},{"name":"Gabby Smalls","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A mobster and police riot gear supervisor on Ceres, leading civilians to shelters.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as a key figure in the Ceres protection racket."},{"name":"Mikey Ko","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A guard who mistook Miller and Holden for Protogen installers, leading to his death at Miller's hands.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's lethal action"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Witness to Miller's confrontation"}],"recentEvents":"Was killed by Miller after revealing details about Protogen's operations on Eros."},{"name":"Mafia Thug","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A violent enforcer killed by Holden during a mob incident.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Holden after firing on civilians."},{"name":"Child Victim","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A thirteen-year-old boy killed by the mafia thug during the chaos on Eros station.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died from a gunshot wound to the chest, rescued by Holden."},{"name":"Mr. Dresden","aliases":["sociopath"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A charismatic corporate executive presenting Protogen's findings on the protomolecule.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Delivered a presentation about the protomolecule as a weapon from an alien civilization."},{"name":"Captain Higgins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Commander of a ship infected by a lethal alien pathogen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Sent a final distress message about crew casualties and the ship's condition before losing contact."},{"name":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","aliases":["Fred Johnson","Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson","Colonel Johnson"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informant"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Negotiated the use of the Rocinante for an Eros mission, revealed the fictional Lionel Polanski, and discussed the data cube."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A stealth ship captured and repurposed, later found to be infected with a deadly biological agent.","recentEvents":"The ship's crew was killed by an unknown pathogen, with Julie Mao's body remaining in an unsealed locker.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was transported here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"The ship's contamination and events on Eros are interconnected."}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"Miller's Grief, Revenge, and Moral Conflict","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The OPA announced the execution of Martian spies via an industrial airlock, framing it as a necessary action for freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden and Miller discuss the protomolecule's data here"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation (Fred Johnson's Role Revealed)","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Holden plans to travel here to seek trusted allies regarding the protomolecule's safe.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked by the Belt's orbital pathways"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden's destination after leaving the ship"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden investigate the ship's engineering deck, discovering signs of a violent takeover and the presence of a mysterious infectious agent.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was captured and held here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Events on Eros Station are linked to the ship's contamination and the crew's fate."}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation (Fred Johnson's Role Revealed)","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"Protogen's Protomolecule Experimentation and Alien Weapon Threat","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station","Maintenance Tunnel","Maintenance Shaft","Eros flophouse","Eros station"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Deployment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A dimly lit service passage carved by early Belters, housing critical power lines and running through the first Belt colony's infrastructure.","recentEvents":"Miller reflects on past events tied to the station, including the death of Juliette Mao and the aftermath of the attack on Deimos.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Part of the Belt's interconnected stations"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Mole activity originated here"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent to the maintenance corridors"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Part of the lockdown area"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Miller and Holden were rescued from Eros Station by the Donnager"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's utility infrastructure"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Miller's temporary residence before departing"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112","Julie's asteroid"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A barren asteroid tethered to a wealthy owner, serving as a navigational warning.","recentEvents":"Holden and the crew of the Rocinante approach it, discovering a stealth ship linked to the Donnager's destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Rocinante is en route to Ceres after analyzing data from this asteroid."}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter","Casino Area"],"description":"A restricted zone on Eros Station where the population is funneled during lockdowns, serving as a central gathering point.","recentEvents":"The level is under lockdown, with guards enforcing movement toward shelters. Miller and Holden use this as a strategic point to regroup.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's structure"}]},{"name":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","aliases":["Radiation Lockdown Zones","Radiation Incubators"],"description":"Sealed-off sections of Eros Station purportedly designed to protect citizens from radiation, but secretly used as containment areas for lethal gas and biological agents.","recentEvents":"The shelters were emptied, leaving only Holden and Miller's footsteps. Ko's body is left here after being shot.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Designated emergency lockdown zones"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via transit corridors"},{"location":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","relationship":"Located nearby"}]},{"name":"Thoth Station","arc":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","description":"A space station where Captain Higgins sent a distress message about the deteriorating condition of his crew and secured materials before the ship's fate.","recentEvents":"Miller obtains its orbital coordinates from Havelock, leading to plans for an assault with the OPA.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"The ship's location is being tracked in the Belt, as per the comm log."},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"The comm log was received on the Rocinante, which is now searching for the ship."},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Linked via secure server cluster"}]},{"name":"Rocinante","aliases":["Roci"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A private ship used by the crew, serving as their mobile base of operations.","recentEvents":"Suffered a direct cannon attack from an enemy fighter, resulting in structural damage and casualties. The crew survived thanks to anti-spalling bulkheads.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Belt's communication networks"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Holden's next destination"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Docked at Thoth Station"}]},{"name":"Nauvoo","aliases":["Generation Ship"],"description":"A massive, half-built generation ship under construction at Tycho Station, serving as a potential vessel for interstellar travel.","recentEvents":"Miller observes its construction and meets Naomi to discuss comm data. He later connects with Havelock via a secure drop site.","relationships":[{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Under construction within Tycho Station's habitat rings"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation (Fred Johnson's Role Revealed)","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]"],"summary":"Holden and Miller confront Fred Johnson's ambiguous OPA allegiance, as Fred acknowledges the protomolecule's existential threat but prioritizes political survival over immediate action, revealing OPA's continued manipulation of interplanetary power dynamics."},{"name":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"Miller's decision to join the assault on Thoth Station marks a shift from passive investigation to active participation, balancing his desire for vengeance against Fred Johnson with ethical doubts about the mission's risks."},{"name":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"The Rocinante sustains critical damage during a high-speed dogfight with a pursuing fighter, forcing the crew to prioritize repairs and evade capture. Holden's team survives the attack but faces ongoing threats from enemy forces and the need to reach Thoth Station's docking facilities."},{"name":"Thoth Station Assault and Protomolecule Threat","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Alex Kamal","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"The crew's attack on Thoth Station escalates as they confront Protogen's stealth frigates and defensive systems, risking exposure of their mission to neutralize the protomolecule research facility."}],"summary":"Holden and the Rocinante crew survive a harrowing attack by an enemy fighter, sustaining significant damage to their ship. They establish contact with Fred Johnson to coordinate a safe landing at a station's dock, highlighting the ongoing tension and survival challenges in the Belt."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":44,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Target of search"}],"recentEvents":"Discovered dead in shower stall with severe biological modifications"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden [aliases: James Holden, Holden]","aliases":["James Holden","Holden","Jim Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station (Rocinante)","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Close ally, whose perspective influences Holden's decisions"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Debates with Miller about broadcasting the protomolecule data"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate and former detective"}],"recentEvents":"Survived a fighter attack on the Rocinante, coordinated with Fred Johnson for docking"},{"name":"Naomi Nagata [aliases: Naomi]","aliases":["Naomi","Naomi Nagata"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station (Rocinante)","description":"Medical officer who tends to Miller and Holden. Engages in a tense conversation with Holden about his feelings for her.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and romantic interest"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate and former detective"}],"recentEvents":"Survived a near-miss cannon strike, assisted in communication with Fred Johnson"},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station (Rocinante)","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Visited Miller's cabin, shared breakfast, and discussed the war's impact"}],"recentEvents":"Commented on the danger of the battle, remained conscious during the attack"},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned by Holden as someone he wished was still alive."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller [aliases: Miller]","aliases":["Miller","Detective Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Former partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"Former romantic partner"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain of the Rocinante, debates with Miller about broadcasting the protomolecule data"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Aboard the Rocinante, with whom Miller discusses ethical dilemmas"},{"character":"Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted police"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Team member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Led an assault on Thoth Station, coordinated with Fred Johnson, and confronted Mr. Dresden."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"OPA","relationship":"Leadership of the OPA's security apparatus"}],"recentEvents":"Announced the execution of Martian spies via a public video feed, emphasizing the OPA's stance on security"},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station (Rocinante)","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member and tactical operator"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Fought off a fighter, reported damage to the Rocinante"},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock [aliases: Havelock]","aliases":["Havelock","Dmitri Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ganymede server cluster","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Former partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided encrypted intel on Thoth Station's location to Miller."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."},{"name":"Guard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A fake riot cop leading civilians to a radiation shelter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nudged by Miller after the shootout."},{"name":"Gabby Smalls","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A mobster and police riot gear supervisor on Ceres, leading civilians to shelters.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as a key figure in the Ceres protection racket."},{"name":"Mikey Ko","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A guard who mistook Miller and Holden for Protogen installers, leading to his death at Miller's hands.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's lethal action"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Witness to Miller's confrontation"}],"recentEvents":"Was killed by Miller after revealing details about Protogen's operations on Eros."},{"name":"Mafia Thug","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A violent enforcer killed by Holden during a mob incident.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Holden after firing on civilians."},{"name":"Child Victim","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A thirteen-year-old boy killed by the mafia thug during the chaos on Eros station.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died from a gunshot wound to the chest, rescued by Holden."},{"name":"Mr. Dresden","aliases":["sociopath"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A charismatic corporate executive presenting Protogen's findings on the protomolecule.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Negotiated surrender terms with Fred Johnson, claimed responsibility for Eros operations."},{"name":"Captain Higgins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Commander of a ship infected by a lethal alien pathogen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Sent a final distress message about crew casualties and the ship's condition before losing contact."},{"name":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","aliases":["Fred Johnson","Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson","Colonel Johnson"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Commander under whom Miller operates"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Directed the assault on Thoth Station and negotiated terms with Mr. Dresden."},{"name":"Diogo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A young Belter militia member in OPA forces during the assault.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Participated in the assault on Thoth Station, was injured by crowd suppression rounds."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A stealth ship captured and repurposed, later found to be infected with a deadly biological agent.","recentEvents":"The ship's crew was killed by an unknown pathogen, with Julie Mao's body remaining in an unsealed locker.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was transported here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"The ship's contamination and events on Eros are interconnected."}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"Miller's Grief, Revenge, and Moral Conflict","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The OPA announced the execution of Martian spies via an industrial airlock, framing it as a necessary action for freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden and Miller discuss the protomolecule's data here"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation (Fred Johnson's Role Revealed)","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Holden plans to travel here to seek trusted allies regarding the protomolecule's safe.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked by the Belt's orbital pathways"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden's destination after leaving the ship"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden investigate the ship's engineering deck, discovering signs of a violent takeover and the presence of a mysterious infectious agent.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was captured and held here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Events on Eros Station are linked to the ship's contamination and the crew's fate."}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"Protogen's Protomolecule Experimentation and Alien Weapon Threat","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station","Maintenance Tunnel","Maintenance Shaft","Eros flophouse","Eros station"],"arc":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","description":"A dimly lit service passage carved by early Belters, housing critical power lines and running through the first Belt colony's infrastructure.","recentEvents":"Miller reflects on past events tied to the station, including the death of Juliette Mao and the aftermath of the attack on Deimos.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Part of the Belt's interconnected stations"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Mole activity originated here"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent to the maintenance corridors"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Part of the lockdown area"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Miller and Holden were rescued from Eros Station by the Donnager"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's utility infrastructure"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Miller's temporary residence before departing"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112","Julie's asteroid"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A barren asteroid tethered to a wealthy owner, serving as a navigational warning.","recentEvents":"Holden and the crew of the Rocinante approach it, discovering a stealth ship linked to the Donnager's destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Rocinante is en route to Ceres after analyzing data from this asteroid."}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter","Casino Area"],"description":"A restricted zone on Eros Station where the population is funneled during lockdowns, serving as a central gathering point.","recentEvents":"The level is under lockdown, with guards enforcing movement toward shelters. Miller and Holden use this as a strategic point to regroup.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's structure"}]},{"name":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","aliases":["Radiation Lockdown Zones","Radiation Incubators"],"description":"Sealed-off sections of Eros Station purportedly designed to protect citizens from radiation, but secretly used as containment areas for lethal gas and biological agents.","recentEvents":"The shelters were emptied, leaving only Holden and Miller's footsteps. Ko's body is left here after being shot.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Designated emergency lockdown zones"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via transit corridors"},{"location":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","relationship":"Located nearby"}]},{"name":"Thoth Station","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A space station where Captain Higgins sent a distress message about the deteriorating condition of his crew and secured materials before the ship's fate.","recentEvents":"Miller obtains its orbital coordinates from Havelock, leading to plans for an assault with the OPA.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"The ship's location is being tracked in the Belt, as per the comm log."},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"The comm log was received on the Rocinante, which is now searching for the ship."},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Linked via secure server cluster"}]},{"name":"Rocinante","aliases":["Roci"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A private ship used by the crew, serving as their mobile base of operations.","recentEvents":"Suffered a direct cannon attack from an enemy fighter, resulting in structural damage and casualties. The crew survived thanks to anti-spalling bulkheads.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Belt's communication networks"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Holden's next destination"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Docked at Thoth Station"}]},{"name":"Nauvoo","aliases":["Generation Ship"],"description":"A massive, half-built generation ship under construction at Tycho Station, serving as a potential vessel for interstellar travel.","recentEvents":"Miller observes its construction and meets Naomi to discuss comm data. He later connects with Havelock via a secure drop site.","relationships":[{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Under construction within Tycho Station's habitat rings"}]},{"name":"Guy Molinari","description":"A military assault ship used to breach Thoth Station during the OPA's coordinated attack.","recentEvents":"Miller and OPA forces launched a breach operation from the Guy Molinari, engaging Protogen security and navigating Thoth Station's defenses.","relationships":[{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Target of the assault"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","Fred Johnson","Dresden","OPA"],"summary":"Holden and Miller confront Fred Johnson's ambiguous OPA allegiance, as Fred acknowledges the protomolecule's existential threat but prioritizes political survival over immediate action, revealing OPA's continued manipulation of interplanetary power dynamics."},{"name":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Diogo","Julie Mao"],"summary":"Miller grapples with the ethical implications of leading an assault while balancing tactical necessity. His decision to take Julie's place in the mission deepens his internal conflict, though his actions during the battle reaffirm his commitment to the OPA's cause."},{"name":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"The Rocinante sustains critical damage during a high-speed dogfight with a pursuing fighter, forcing the crew to prioritize repairs and evade capture. Holden's team survives the attack but faces ongoing threats from enemy forces and the need to reach Thoth Station's docking facilities."},{"name":"Thoth Station Assault and OPA Negotiation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Alex Kamal","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"The crew's attack on Thoth Station escalates as they confront Protogen's stealth frigates and defensive systems, risking exposure of their mission to neutralize the protomolecule research facility."},{"name":"Thoth Station Assault and Protomolecule Threat","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Fred Johnson","Dresden","OPA"],"summary":"The OPA's assault on Thoth Station reaches the operations center, where Miller and Fred Johnson confront Protogen security and negotiate with Dresden. The battle highlights tactical challenges and the station's deceptive design, while the Protomolecule's presence looms as an unresolved threat."}],"summary":"Miller leads an OPA assault on Thoth Station, battling Protogen security and navigating the station's defenses. The attack culminates in a tense negotiation between Fred and Dresden, with the OPA securing control of the station's operations center."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":45,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Target of search"}],"recentEvents":"Discovered dead in shower stall with severe biological modifications"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden [aliases: James Holden, Holden]","aliases":["James Holden","Holden","Jim Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station (Rocinante)","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Close ally, whose perspective influences Holden's decisions"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Debates with Miller about broadcasting the protomolecule data"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate and former detective"}],"recentEvents":"Survived a fighter attack on the Rocinante, coordinated with Fred Johnson for docking"},{"name":"Naomi Nagata [aliases: Naomi]","aliases":["Naomi","Naomi Nagata"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station (Rocinante)","description":"Medical officer who tends to Miller and Holden. Engages in a tense conversation with Holden about his feelings for her.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and romantic interest"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate and former detective"}],"recentEvents":"Survived a near-miss cannon strike, assisted in communication with Fred Johnson"},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station (Rocinante)","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Visited Miller's cabin, shared breakfast, and discussed the war's impact"}],"recentEvents":"Commented on the danger of the battle, remained conscious during the attack"},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned by Holden as someone he wished was still alive."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller [aliases: Miller]","aliases":["Miller","Detective Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Former partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"Former romantic partner"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain of the Rocinante, debates with Miller about broadcasting the protomolecule data"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Aboard the Rocinante, with whom Miller discusses ethical dilemmas"},{"character":"Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted police"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Team member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Led an assault on Thoth Station, coordinated with Fred Johnson, and confronted Mr. Dresden."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"OPA","relationship":"Leadership of the OPA's security apparatus"}],"recentEvents":"Announced the execution of Martian spies via a public video feed, emphasizing the OPA's stance on security"},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station (Rocinante)","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member and tactical operator"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Fought off a fighter, reported damage to the Rocinante"},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock [aliases: Havelock]","aliases":["Havelock","Dmitri Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ganymede server cluster","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Former partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided encrypted intel on Thoth Station's location to Miller."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."},{"name":"Guard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A fake riot cop leading civilians to a radiation shelter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nudged by Miller after the shootout."},{"name":"Gabby Smalls","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A mobster and police riot gear supervisor on Ceres, leading civilians to shelters.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as a key figure in the Ceres protection racket."},{"name":"Mikey Ko","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A guard who mistook Miller and Holden for Protogen installers, leading to his death at Miller's hands.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's lethal action"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Witness to Miller's confrontation"}],"recentEvents":"Was killed by Miller after revealing details about Protogen's operations on Eros."},{"name":"Mafia Thug","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A violent enforcer killed by Holden during a mob incident.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Holden after firing on civilians."},{"name":"Child Victim","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A thirteen-year-old boy killed by the mafia thug during the chaos on Eros station.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died from a gunshot wound to the chest, rescued by Holden."},{"name":"Mr. Dresden","aliases":["sociopath"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A charismatic corporate executive presenting Protogen's findings on the protomolecule.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Negotiated surrender terms with Fred Johnson, claimed responsibility for Eros operations."},{"name":"Captain Higgins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Commander of a ship infected by a lethal alien pathogen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Sent a final distress message about crew casualties and the ship's condition before losing contact."},{"name":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","aliases":["Fred Johnson","Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson","Colonel Johnson"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Commander under whom Miller operates"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications contact"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Directed the assault on Thoth Station and negotiated terms with Mr. Dresden."},{"name":"Diogo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A young Belter militia member in OPA forces during the assault.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Participated in the assault on Thoth Station, was injured by crowd suppression rounds."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A stealth ship captured and repurposed, later found to be infected with a deadly biological agent.","recentEvents":"The ship's crew was killed by an unknown pathogen, with Julie Mao's body remaining in an unsealed locker.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was transported here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"The ship's contamination and events on Eros are interconnected."}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"Miller's Grief, Revenge, and Moral Conflict","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The OPA announced the execution of Martian spies via an industrial airlock, framing it as a necessary action for freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden and Miller discuss the protomolecule's data here"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation (Fred Johnson's Role Revealed)","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Holden plans to travel here to seek trusted allies regarding the protomolecule's safe.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked by the Belt's orbital pathways"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden's destination after leaving the ship"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden investigate the ship's engineering deck, discovering signs of a violent takeover and the presence of a mysterious infectious agent.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was captured and held here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Events on Eros Station are linked to the ship's contamination and the crew's fate."}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"Protogen's Protomolecule Experimentation and Alien Weapon Threat","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station","Maintenance Tunnel","Maintenance Shaft","Eros flophouse","Eros station"],"arc":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","description":"A dimly lit service passage carved by early Belters, housing critical power lines and running through the first Belt colony's infrastructure.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as the site of the protomolecule's activation and the deaths of millions, referenced in Dresden's justification for its use.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Part of the Belt's interconnected stations"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Mole activity originated here"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent to the maintenance corridors"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Part of the lockdown area"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Miller and Holden were rescued from Eros Station by the Donnager"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's utility infrastructure"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Miller's temporary residence before departing"},{"location":"Protogen","relationship":"Site of the protomolecule's initial deployment"},{"location":"OPA","relationship":"Target of Protogen's operations"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112","Julie's asteroid"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A barren asteroid tethered to a wealthy owner, serving as a navigational warning.","recentEvents":"Holden and the crew of the Rocinante approach it, discovering a stealth ship linked to the Donnager's destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Rocinante is en route to Ceres after analyzing data from this asteroid."}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter","Casino Area"],"description":"A restricted zone on Eros Station where the population is funneled during lockdowns, serving as a central gathering point.","recentEvents":"The level is under lockdown, with guards enforcing movement toward shelters. Miller and Holden use this as a strategic point to regroup.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's structure"}]},{"name":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","aliases":["Radiation Lockdown Zones","Radiation Incubators"],"description":"Sealed-off sections of Eros Station purportedly designed to protect citizens from radiation, but secretly used as containment areas for lethal gas and biological agents.","recentEvents":"The shelters were emptied, leaving only Holden and Miller's footsteps. Ko's body is left here after being shot.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Designated emergency lockdown zones"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via transit corridors"},{"location":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","relationship":"Located nearby"}]},{"name":"Thoth Station","aliases":["Thoth"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A space station where Captain Higgins sent a distress message about the deteriorating condition of his crew and secured materials before the ship's fate.","recentEvents":"Holden and his crew docked here after the Rocinante's damage, confronted Antony Dresden, and learned about Protogen's plans with the protomolecule.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"The ship's location is being tracked in the Belt, as per the comm log."},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"The comm log was received on the Rocinante, which is now searching for the ship."},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Linked via secure server cluster"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via OPA operations"}]},{"name":"Rocinante","aliases":["Roci"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A private ship used by the crew, serving as their mobile base of operations.","recentEvents":"Suffered a direct cannon attack from an enemy fighter, resulting in structural damage and casualties. The crew survived thanks to anti-spalling bulkheads.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Belt's communication networks"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Holden's next destination"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Docked at Thoth Station"}]},{"name":"Nauvoo","aliases":["Generation Ship"],"description":"A massive, half-built generation ship under construction at Tycho Station, serving as a potential vessel for interstellar travel.","recentEvents":"Miller observes its construction and meets Naomi to discuss comm data. He later connects with Havelock via a secure drop site.","relationships":[{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Under construction within Tycho Station's habitat rings"}]},{"name":"Guy Molinari","description":"A military assault ship used to breach Thoth Station during the OPA's coordinated attack.","recentEvents":"Miller and OPA forces launched a breach operation from the Guy Molinari, engaging Protogen security and navigating Thoth Station's defenses.","relationships":[{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Target of the assault"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","Fred Johnson","Dresden","OPA"],"summary":"Holden and Miller confront Fred Johnson's ambiguous OPA allegiance, as Fred acknowledges the protomolecule's existential threat but prioritizes political survival over immediate action, revealing OPA's continued manipulation of interplanetary power dynamics."},{"name":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Diogo","Julie Mao"],"summary":"Miller grapples with the ethical implications of leading an assault while balancing tactical necessity. His decision to take Julie's place in the mission deepens his internal conflict, though his actions during the battle reaffirm his commitment to the OPA's cause."},{"name":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"The Rocinante sustains critical damage during a high-speed dogfight with a pursuing fighter, forcing the crew to prioritize repairs and evade capture. Holden's team survives the attack but faces ongoing threats from enemy forces and the need to reach Thoth Station's docking facilities."},{"name":"Thoth Station Assault and OPA Negotiation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Alex Kamal","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"The crew's attack on Thoth Station escalates as they confront Protogen's stealth frigates and defensive systems, risking exposure of their mission to neutralize the protomolecule research facility."},{"name":"Thoth Station Assault and Protomolecule Threat","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Fred Johnson","Dresden","OPA"],"summary":"The OPA's assault on Thoth Station reaches the operations center, where Miller and Fred Johnson confront Protogen security and negotiate with Dresden. The battle highlights tactical challenges and the station's deceptive design, while the Protomolecule's presence looms as an unresolved threat."}],"summary":"Holden and his crew arrive at Thoth Station after the Rocinante's catastrophic damage, where they confront Antony Dresden and learn about Protogen's plans to weaponize the protomolecule. Tensions rise as Dresden justifies the mass casualties on Eros as necessary for humanity's evolution, leaving Holden morally conflicted but unable to fully reject the argument. The OPA's control over the station remains precarious as the battle for Eros' data intensifies."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":46,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Former associate, now present at Thoth Station"}],"recentEvents":"Sitting with Miller after the Thoth Station incident, offering comfort."},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden [aliases: James Holden, Holden]","aliases":["James Holden","Holden","Jim Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Close ally, whose perspective influences Holden's decisions"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Debates with Miller about broadcasting the protomolecule data"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate and former detective"}],"recentEvents":"Confronted Miller over the killing of Dresden, expressed outrage, and left Thoth Station."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata [aliases: Naomi]","aliases":["Naomi","Naomi Nagata"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Medical officer who tends to Miller and Holden. Engages in a tense conversation with Holden about his feelings for her.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and romantic interest"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate and former detective"},{"character":"Detecty Miller","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Interacted with Miller at a bar on Tycho Station, discussing the aftermath of the Thoth Station incident."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Visited Miller's cabin, shared breakfast, and discussed the war's impact"}],"recentEvents":"Interacted with Miller at a bar on Tycho Station, discussing the aftermath of the Thoth Station incident."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned by Holden as someone he wished was still alive."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller [aliases: Miller]","aliases":["Miller","Detective Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Former partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"Former romantic partner"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain of the Rocinante, debates with Miller about broadcasting the protomolecule data"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Aboard the Rocinante, with whom Miller discusses ethical dilemmas"},{"character":"Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted police"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Team member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"OPA commander, colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed Dresden, faced backlash from Holden, and left Thoth Station with Fred Johnson."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"OPA","relationship":"Leadership of the OPA's security apparatus"}],"recentEvents":"Announced the execution of Martian spies via a public video feed, emphasizing the OPA's stance on security"},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station (Rocinante)","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member and tactical operator"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Fought off a fighter, reported damage to the Rocinante"},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock [aliases: Havelock]","aliases":["Havelock","Dmitri Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ganymede server cluster","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Former partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided encrypted intel on Thoth Station's location to Miller."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."},{"name":"Guard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A fake riot cop leading civilians to a radiation shelter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nudged by Miller after the shootout."},{"name":"Gabby Smalls","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A mobster and police riot gear supervisor on Ceres, leading civilians to shelters.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as a key figure in the Ceres protection racket."},{"name":"Mikey Ko","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A guard who mistook Miller and Holden for Protogen installers, leading to his death at Miller's hands.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's lethal action"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Witness to Miller's confrontation"}],"recentEvents":"Was killed by Miller after revealing details about Protogen's operations on Eros."},{"name":"Mafia Thug","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A violent enforcer killed by Holden during a mob incident.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Holden after firing on civilians."},{"name":"Child Victim","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A thirteen-year-old boy killed by the mafia thug during the chaos on Eros station.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died from a gunshot wound to the chest, rescued by Holden."},{"name":"Mr. Dresden","aliases":["sociopath","Dresden"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A former Protogen scientist and antagonist, killed by Miller during the Thoth Station incident.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's actions"}],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Miller, with his corpse serving as a catalyst for moral conflict."},{"name":"Captain Higgins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Commander of a ship infected by a lethal alien pathogen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Sent a final distress message about crew casualties and the ship's condition before losing contact."},{"name":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","aliases":["Fred Johnson","Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson","Colonel Johnson"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Commander under whom Miller operates"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander of the Rocinante"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the team to resume work after the Thoth Station incident, mediating tensions between Miller and Holden."},{"name":"Diogo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"A Belter and friend of Miller, providing a temporary place to stay.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Hosted Miller in his apartment on Tycho Station after the Thoth Station incident."},{"name":"OPA soldiers","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Members of the OPA involved in the Thoth Station occupation.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Present during the shooting of Dresden, surprised by the violence."}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A stealth ship captured and repurposed, later found to be infected with a deadly biological agent.","recentEvents":"The ship's crew was killed by an unknown pathogen, with Julie Mao's body remaining in an unsealed locker.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was transported here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"The ship's contamination and events on Eros are interconnected."}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"Miller's Grief, Revenge, and Moral Conflict","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The OPA announced the execution of Martian spies via an industrial airlock, framing it as a necessary action for freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden and Miller discuss the protomolecule's data here"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation (Fred Johnson's Role Revealed)","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Miller returned to Tycho after Thoth, where he encountered fellow Thoth survivors and witnessed decrypted footage of the protomolecule's transformation of Eros.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked by the Belt's orbital pathways"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden's destination after leaving the ship"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Miller's temporary base after leaving Thoth"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Protomolecule activity was decrypted from Eros feeds"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden investigate the ship's engineering deck, discovering signs of a violent takeover and the presence of a mysterious infectious agent.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was captured and held here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Events on Eros Station are linked to the ship's contamination and the crew's fate."}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"Protogen's Protomolecule Experimentation and Alien Weapon Threat","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station","Maintenance Tunnel","Maintenance Shaft","Eros flophouse","Eros station"],"arc":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","description":"A dimly lit service passage carved by early Belters, housing critical power lines and running through the first Belt colony's infrastructure.","recentEvents":"Decrypted feeds showed the protomolecule's transformation of Eros into a hive of grotesque, mutating entities, with Juliette Mao's corpse as a focal point.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Part of the Belt's interconnected stations"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Miller viewed decrypted Eros footage here"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent to the maintenance corridors"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Part of the lockdown area"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Miller and Holden were rescued from Eros Station by the Donnager"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's utility infrastructure"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Miller's temporary residence before departing"},{"location":"Protogen","relationship":"Site of the protomolecule's initial deployment"},{"location":"OPA","relationship":"Target of Protogen's operations"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Protomolecule activity was revealed through Eros feeds"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112","Julie's asteroid"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A barren asteroid tethered to a wealthy owner, serving as a navigational warning.","recentEvents":"Holden and the crew of the Rocinante approach it, discovering a stealth ship linked to the Donnager's destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Rocinante is en route to Ceres after analyzing data from this asteroid."}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter","Casino Area"],"description":"A restricted zone on Eros Station where the population is funneled during lockdowns, serving as a central gathering point.","recentEvents":"The level is under lockdown, with guards enforcing movement toward shelters. Miller and Holden use this as a strategic point to regroup.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's structure"}]},{"name":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","aliases":["Radiation Lockdown Zones","Radiation Incubators"],"description":"Sealed-off sections of Eros Station purportedly designed to protect citizens from radiation, but secretly used as containment areas for lethal gas and biological agents.","recentEvents":"The shelters were emptied, leaving only Holden and Miller's footsteps. Ko's body is left here after being shot.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Designated emergency lockdown zones"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via transit corridors"},{"location":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","relationship":"Located nearby"}]},{"name":"Thoth Station","aliases":["Thoth"],"arc":"Thoth Station Assault and Protomolecule Spread","description":"A space station where Captain Higgins sent a distress message about the deteriorating condition of his crew and secured materials before the ship's fate.","recentEvents":"Miller executed captured Protogen scientist Dresden in cold blood, sparking tension with Holden. OPA forces skeletonized the station before evacuating it, revealing the protomolecule's presence in hidden feeds.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"The ship's location is being tracked in the Belt, as per the comm log."},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"The comm log was received on the Rocinante, which is now searching for the ship."},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Linked via secure server cluster"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via OPA operations"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Miller is now stationed here after leaving Thoth"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Protomolecule activity was decrypted from Eros feeds"}]},{"name":"Rocinante","aliases":["Roci"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A private ship used by the crew, serving as their mobile base of operations.","recentEvents":"Suffered a direct cannon attack from an enemy fighter, resulting in structural damage and casualties. The crew survived thanks to anti-spalling bulkheads.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Belt's communication networks"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Holden's next destination"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Docked at Thoth Station"}]},{"name":"Nauvoo","aliases":["Generation Ship"],"description":"A massive, half-built generation ship under construction at Tycho Station, serving as a potential vessel for interstellar travel.","recentEvents":"Miller observes its construction and meets Naomi to discuss comm data. He later connects with Havelock via a secure drop site.","relationships":[{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Under construction within Tycho Station's habitat rings"}]},{"name":"Guy Molinari","description":"A military assault ship used to breach Thoth Station during the OPA's coordinated attack.","recentEvents":"Miller and OPA forces launched a breach operation from the Guy Molinari, engaging Protogen security and navigating Thoth Station's defenses.","relationships":[{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Target of the assault"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","Fred Johnson","Dresden","OPA"],"summary":"Holden and Miller confront Fred Johnson's ambiguous OPA allegiance, as Fred acknowledges the protomolecule's existential threat but prioritizes political survival over immediate action, revealing OPA's continued manipulation of interplanetary power dynamics."},{"name":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Holden","Fred Johnson"],"summary":"Miller's execution of Dresden sparks outrage from Holden and the crew, exposing the ethical chasm between his pragmatic survival instincts and the OPA's ideological justifications, while Fred Johnson's calculated detachment underscores the OPA's cold pragmatism."},{"name":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Amos","Alex"],"summary":"The Rocinante's repairs progress, but the crew faces mounting pressure from OPA control and the protomolecule's spread, with Holden's leadership tested by conflicting loyalties and the looming threat of Earth's retaliation."},{"name":"Thoth Station Assault and OPA Negotiation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Alex Kamal","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"The crew's attack on Thoth Station escalates as they confront Protogen's stealth frigates and defensive systems, risking exposure of their mission to neutralize the protomolecule research facility."},{"name":"Thoth Station Assault and Protomolecule Spread","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Holden","Fred Johnson","Naomi","Amos"],"summary":"The OPA's occupation of Thoth Station accelerates as Miller oversees prisoner control, but the protomolecule's spread through the station's systems and bodies becomes undeniable, forcing the crew to confront its existential threat beyond mere containment."}],"summary":"Miller's brutal execution of Protogen scientist Dresden on Thoth Station sparks conflict with Holden, while OPA forces evacuate the station before its destruction. Returning to Tycho, Miller witnesses decrypted footage of the protomolecule's grotesque transformation of Eros, revealing the true scale of the crisis. The narrative underscores the moral ambiguity of survival in a war where humanity's boundaries are being redefined."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":47,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Former associate, now present at Thoth Station"}],"recentEvents":"Sitting with Miller after the Thoth Station incident, offering comfort."},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden [aliases: James Holden, Holden]","aliases":["James Holden","Holden","Jim Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Close ally, whose perspective influences Holden's decisions"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Debates with Miller about broadcasting the protomolecule data"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate and former detective"}],"recentEvents":"Reviewed repair progress, confronted Miller about past actions, and discussed plans with Naomi"},{"name":"Naomi Nagata [aliases: Naomi]","aliases":["Naomi","Naomi Nagata"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Medical officer who tends to Miller and Holden. Engages in a tense conversation with Holden about his feelings for her.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and romantic interest"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate and former detective"},{"character":"Detecty Miller","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Interacted with Miller at a bar on Tycho Station, discussing the aftermath of the Thoth Station incident."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Visited Miller's cabin, shared breakfast, and discussed the war's impact"}],"recentEvents":"Interacted with Miller at a bar on Tycho Station, discussing the aftermath of the Thoth Station incident."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned by Holden as someone he wished was still alive."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller [aliases: Miller]","aliases":["Miller","Detective Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Former partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"Former romantic partner"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain of the Rocinante, debates with Miller about broadcasting the protomolecule data"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Aboard the Rocinante, with whom Miller discusses ethical dilemmas"},{"character":"Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted police"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Team member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"OPA commander, colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Confronted Holden about past actions, discussed moral ambiguity in justice"},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"OPA","relationship":"Leadership of the OPA's security apparatus"}],"recentEvents":"Announced the execution of Martian spies via a public video feed, emphasizing the OPA's stance on security"},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station (Rocinante)","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member and tactical operator"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Fought off a fighter, reported damage to the Rocinante"},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock [aliases: Havelock]","aliases":["Havelock","Dmitri Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ganymede server cluster","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Former partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided encrypted intel on Thoth Station's location to Miller."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."},{"name":"Guard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A fake riot cop leading civilians to a radiation shelter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nudged by Miller after the shootout."},{"name":"Gabby Smalls","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A mobster and police riot gear supervisor on Ceres, leading civilians to shelters.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as a key figure in the Ceres protection racket."},{"name":"Mikey Ko","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A guard who mistook Miller and Holden for Protogen installers, leading to his death at Miller's hands.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's lethal action"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Witness to Miller's confrontation"}],"recentEvents":"Was killed by Miller after revealing details about Protogen's operations on Eros."},{"name":"Mafia Thug","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A violent enforcer killed by Holden during a mob incident.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Holden after firing on civilians."},{"name":"Child Victim","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A thirteen-year-old boy killed by the mafia thug during the chaos on Eros station.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died from a gunshot wound to the chest, rescued by Holden."},{"name":"Mr. Dresden","aliases":["sociopath","Dresden"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A former Protogen scientist and antagonist, killed by Miller during the Thoth Station incident.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's actions"}],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Miller, with his corpse serving as a catalyst for moral conflict."},{"name":"Captain Higgins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Commander of a ship infected by a lethal alien pathogen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Sent a final distress message about crew casualties and the ship's condition before losing contact."},{"name":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","aliases":["Fred Johnson","Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson","Colonel Johnson"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Commander under whom Miller operates"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander of the Rocinante"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Facilitated crew accommodations during ship repairs"},{"name":"Diogo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"A Belter and friend of Miller, providing a temporary place to stay.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Hosted Miller in his apartment on Tycho Station after the Thoth Station incident."},{"name":"OPA soldiers","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Members of the OPA involved in the Thoth Station occupation.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Present during the shooting of Dresden, surprised by the violence."},{"name":"Sam","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Team leader on the Rocinante repair project, known for her mechanical skills and dry humor","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Respects her work on the Rocinante"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Friendly rivalry and camaraderie"}],"recentEvents":"Completed critical repairs on the Rocinante, engaged in banter with Holden and Naomi about the Golgo game"}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A stealth ship captured and repurposed, later found to be infected with a deadly biological agent.","recentEvents":"The ship's crew was killed by an unknown pathogen, with Julie Mao's body remaining in an unsealed locker.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was transported here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"The ship's contamination and events on Eros are interconnected."}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"Miller's Grief, Revenge, and Moral Conflict","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The OPA announced the execution of Martian spies via an industrial airlock, framing it as a necessary action for freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden and Miller discuss the protomolecule's data here"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation (Fred Johnson's Role Revealed)","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Miller returned to Tycho after Thoth, where he encountered fellow Thoth survivors and witnessed decrypted footage of the protomolecule's transformation of Eros.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked by the Belt's orbital pathways"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden's destination after leaving the ship"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Miller's temporary base after leaving Thoth"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Protomolecule activity was decrypted from Eros feeds"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden investigate the ship's engineering deck, discovering signs of a violent takeover and the presence of a mysterious infectious agent.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was captured and held here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Events on Eros Station are linked to the ship's contamination and the crew's fate."}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station","Maintenance Tunnel","Maintenance Shaft","Eros flophouse","Eros station"],"arc":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","description":"A dimly lit service passage carved by early Belters, housing critical power lines and running through the first Belt colony's infrastructure.","recentEvents":"Holden reflects on the crisis as Earth's war against Mars escalates, with Eros Station suffering catastrophic losses.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Part of the Belt's interconnected stations"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Linked via OPA operations and the broader Belt conflict"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent to the maintenance corridors"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Part of the lockdown area"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Miller and Holden were rescued from Eros Station by the Donnager"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's utility infrastructure"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Miller's temporary residence before departing"},{"location":"Protogen","relationship":"Site of the protomolecule's initial deployment"},{"location":"OPA","relationship":"Target of Protogen's operations"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Protomolecule activity was revealed through Eros feeds"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112","Julie's asteroid"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A barren asteroid tethered to a wealthy owner, serving as a navigational warning.","recentEvents":"Holden and the crew of the Rocinante approach it, discovering a stealth ship linked to the Donnager's destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Rocinante is en route to Ceres after analyzing data from this asteroid."}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter","Casino Area"],"description":"A restricted zone on Eros Station where the population is funneled during lockdowns, serving as a central gathering point.","recentEvents":"The level is under lockdown, with guards enforcing movement toward shelters. Miller and Holden use this as a strategic point to regroup.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's structure"}]},{"name":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","aliases":["Radiation Lockdown Zones","Radiation Incubators"],"description":"Sealed-off sections of Eros Station purportedly designed to protect citizens from radiation, but secretly used as containment areas for lethal gas and biological agents.","recentEvents":"The shelters were emptied, leaving only Holden and Miller's footsteps. Ko's body is left here after being shot.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Designated emergency lockdown zones"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via transit corridors"},{"location":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","relationship":"Located nearby"}]},{"name":"Thoth Station","aliases":["Thoth"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A space station where Captain Higgins sent a distress message about the deteriorating condition of his crew and secured materials before the ship's fate.","recentEvents":"Miller executed captured Protogen scientist Dresden in cold blood, sparking tension with Holden. OPA forces skeletonized the station before evacuating it, revealing the protomolecule's presence in hidden feeds.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"The ship's location is being tracked in the Belt, as per the comm log."},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"The comm log was received on the Rocinante, which is now searching for the ship."},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Linked via secure server cluster"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via OPA operations"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Miller is now stationed here after leaving Thoth"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Protomolecule activity was decrypted from Eros feeds"}]},{"name":"Rocinante","aliases":["Roci"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A private ship used by the crew, serving as their mobile base of operations.","recentEvents":"Suffered a direct cannon attack from an enemy fighter, resulting in structural damage and casualties. The crew survived thanks to anti-spalling bulkheads.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Belt's communication networks"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Holden's next destination"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Docked at Thoth Station"}]},{"name":"Nauvoo","aliases":["Generation Ship"],"description":"A massive, half-built generation ship under construction at Tycho Station, serving as a potential vessel for interstellar travel.","recentEvents":"Miller observes its construction and meets Naomi to discuss comm data. He later connects with Havelock via a secure drop site.","relationships":[{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Under construction within Tycho Station's habitat rings"}]},{"name":"Guy Molinari","description":"A military assault ship used to breach Thoth Station during the OPA's coordinated attack.","recentEvents":"Miller and OPA forces launched a breach operation from the Guy Molinari, engaging Protogen security and navigating Thoth Station's defenses.","relationships":[{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Target of the assault"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","Fred Johnson","Dresden","OPA"],"summary":"Holden and Miller confront Fred Johnson's ambiguous OPA allegiance, as Fred acknowledges the protomolecule's existential threat but prioritizes political survival over immediate action, revealing OPA's continued manipulation of interplanetary power dynamics."},{"name":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller"],"summary":"Holden confronts Miller about Dresden's execution, exposing their unresolved ethical rift over justice vs. survival, while Miller's admission of doubt about Dresden's guilt complicates their dynamic."},{"name":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Sam"],"summary":"Holden grapples with guilt over crew losses and the OPA's role in the war, while Naomi's romantic overture offers fleeting hope amid the looming threat of Earth-Mars conflict."},{"name":"Thoth Station Assault and OPA Negotiation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Alex Kamal","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"The crew's attack on Thoth Station escalates as they confront Protogen's stealth frigates and defensive systems, risking exposure of their mission to neutralize the protomolecule research facility."},{"name":"Thoth Station Assault and Protomolecule Spread","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Detective Miller","OPA soldiers"],"summary":"The protomolecule's spread through Thoth Station intensifies, forcing Holden to balance OPA containment efforts with the crew's escape plans as OPA's bioweapon control remains unchallenged."}],"summary":"Holden navigates life at Thoth Station while grappling with the moral weight of past actions, including the death of Dresden. He confronts Detective Miller's guilt over killing a war criminal, while Naomi hints at rekindling their relationship. Meanwhile, the war between Earth and Mars intensifies, with Eros Station bearing the brunt of Earth's assault, leaving Holden torn between justice and the cost of vengeance."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":48,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao","Juliette Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Former associate, now present at Thoth Station"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in internal dialogue with Miller about his past actions and future"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden [aliases: James Holden, Holden]","aliases":["James Holden","Holden","Jim Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Executive officer of the Canterbury, a colony transport ship. A former Earth navy officer with a cynical view of Belters and their physiology.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Close ally, whose perspective influences Holden's decisions"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Debates with Miller about broadcasting the protomolecule data"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate and former detective"}],"recentEvents":"Reviewed repair progress, confronted Miller about past actions, and discussed plans with Naomi"},{"name":"Naomi Nagata [aliases: Naomi]","aliases":["Naomi","Naomi Nagata"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Medical officer who tends to Miller and Holden. Engages in a tense conversation with Holden about his feelings for her.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and romantic interest"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate and former detective"},{"character":"Detecty Miller","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Interacted with Miller at a bar on Tycho Station, discussing the aftermath of the Thoth Station incident."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Visited Miller's cabin, shared breakfast, and discussed the war's impact"}],"recentEvents":"Interacted with Miller at a bar on Tycho Station, discussing the aftermath of the Thoth Station incident."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned by Holden as someone he wished was still alive."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller [aliases: Miller]","aliases":["Miller","Detective Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Former partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"Former romantic partner"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain of the Rocinante, debates with Miller about broadcasting the protomolecule data"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Aboard the Rocinante, with whom Miller discusses ethical dilemmas"},{"character":"Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted police"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Team member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Military contact seeking his expertise"},{"character":"Juliette Mao","relationship":"Former lover and partner in crime"}],"recentEvents":"Sought employment with Fred Johnson, discussed protomolecule containment strategies, and engaged in introspective dialogue with Juliette Mao"},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"OPA","relationship":"Leadership of the OPA's security apparatus"}],"recentEvents":"Announced the execution of Martian spies via a public video feed, emphasizing the OPA's stance on security"},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station (Rocinante)","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member and tactical operator"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Fought off a fighter, reported damage to the Rocinante"},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock [aliases: Havelock]","aliases":["Havelock","Dmitri Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ganymede server cluster","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Former partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided encrypted intel on Thoth Station's location to Miller."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."},{"name":"Guard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A fake riot cop leading civilians to a radiation shelter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nudged by Miller after the shootout."},{"name":"Gabby Smalls","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A mobster and police riot gear supervisor on Ceres, leading civilians to shelters.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as a key figure in the Ceres protection racket."},{"name":"Mikey Ko","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A guard who mistook Miller and Holden for Protogen installers, leading to his death at Miller's hands.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's lethal action"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Witness to Miller's confrontation"}],"recentEvents":"Was killed by Miller after revealing details about Protogen's operations on Eros."},{"name":"Mafia Thug","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A violent enforcer killed by Holden during a mob incident.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Holden after firing on civilians."},{"name":"Child Victim","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A thirteen-year-old boy killed by the mafia thug during the chaos on Eros station.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died from a gunshot wound to the chest, rescued by Holden."},{"name":"Mr. Dresden","aliases":["sociopath","Dresden"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A former Protogen scientist and antagonist, killed by Miller during the Thoth Station incident.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's actions"}],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Miller, with his corpse serving as a catalyst for moral conflict."},{"name":"Captain Higgins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Commander of a ship infected by a lethal alien pathogen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Sent a final distress message about crew casualties and the ship's condition before losing contact."},{"name":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","aliases":["Fred Johnson","Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson","Colonel Johnson"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Military contact seeking his expertise"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander of the Rocinante"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Offered Miller a security consultant position and discussed protomolecule containment strategies"},{"name":"Diogo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A Belter and friend of Miller, providing a temporary place to stay.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informant and potential employer"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a job opportunity and discussed Eros Station's mysterious broadcasts"},{"name":"OPA soldiers","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Members of the OPA involved in the Thoth Station occupation.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Present during the shooting of Dresden, surprised by the violence."},{"name":"Sam","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Team leader on the Rocinante repair project, known for her mechanical skills and dry humor","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Respects her work on the Rocinante"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Friendly rivalry and camaraderie"}],"recentEvents":"Completed critical repairs on the Rocinante, engaged in banter with Holden and Naomi about the Golgo game"},{"name":"Manager","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A weedy, disheveled office manager in Tycho Station","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Rejected Miller's job application for a security guard position"}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A stealth ship captured and repurposed, later found to be infected with a deadly biological agent.","recentEvents":"The ship's crew was killed by an unknown pathogen, with Julie Mao's body remaining in an unsealed locker.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was transported here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"The ship's contamination and events on Eros are interconnected."}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The OPA announced the execution of Martian spies via an industrial airlock, framing it as a necessary action for freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden and Miller discuss the protomolecule's data here"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation (Fred Johnson's Role Revealed)","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Miller returned to Tycho after Thoth, where he encountered fellow Thoth survivors and witnessed decrypted footage of the protomolecule's transformation of Eros.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked by the Belt's orbital pathways"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden's destination after leaving the ship"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Miller's temporary base after leaving Thoth"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Protomolecule activity was decrypted from Eros feeds"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden investigate the ship's engineering deck, discovering signs of a violent takeover and the presence of a mysterious infectious agent.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was captured and held here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Events on Eros Station are linked to the ship's contamination and the crew's fate."}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station","Maintenance Tunnel","Maintenance Shaft","Eros flophouse","Eros station"],"arc":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","description":"A dimly lit service passage carved by early Belters, housing critical power lines and running through the first Belt colony's infrastructure.","recentEvents":"Miller listens to dying system voices from Eros, discussing the protomolecule's effects and its potential to spread. Fred Johnson considers destroying Eros to prevent its proliferation.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Part of the Belt's interconnected stations"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Linked via OPA operations and the broader Belt conflict"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent to the maintenance corridors"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Part of the lockdown area"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Miller and Holden were rescued from Eros Station by the Donnager"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's utility infrastructure"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Miller's temporary residence before departing"},{"location":"Protogen","relationship":"Site of the protomolecule's initial deployment"},{"location":"OPA","relationship":"Target of Protogen's operations"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Protomolecule activity was revealed through Eros feeds"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112","Julie's asteroid"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A barren asteroid tethered to a wealthy owner, serving as a navigational warning.","recentEvents":"Holden and the crew of the Rocinante approach it, discovering a stealth ship linked to the Donnager's destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Rocinante is en route to Ceres after analyzing data from this asteroid."}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter","Casino Area"],"description":"A restricted zone on Eros Station where the population is funneled during lockdowns, serving as a central gathering point.","recentEvents":"The level is under lockdown, with guards enforcing movement toward shelters. Miller and Holden use this as a strategic point to regroup.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's structure"}]},{"name":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","aliases":["Radiation Lockdown Zones","Radiation Incubators"],"description":"Sealed-off sections of Eros Station purportedly designed to protect citizens from radiation, but secretly used as containment areas for lethal gas and biological agents.","recentEvents":"The shelters were emptied, leaving only Holden and Miller's footsteps. Ko's body is left here after being shot.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Designated emergency lockdown zones"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via transit corridors"},{"location":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","relationship":"Located nearby"}]},{"name":"Thoth Station","aliases":["Thoth"],"arc":"Thoth Station Assault and Protomolecule Spread","description":"A space station where Captain Higgins sent a distress message about the deteriorating condition of his crew and secured materials before the ship's fate.","recentEvents":"Miller executed captured Protogen scientist Dresden in cold blood, sparking tension with Holden. OPA forces skeletonized the station before evacuating it, revealing the protomolecule's presence in hidden feeds.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"The ship's location is being tracked in the Belt, as per the comm log."},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"The comm log was received on the Rocinante, which is now searching for the ship."},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Linked via secure server cluster"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via OPA operations"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Miller is now stationed here after leaving Thoth"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Protomolecule activity was decrypted from Eros feeds"}]},{"name":"Rocinante","aliases":["Roci"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A private ship used by the crew, serving as their mobile base of operations.","recentEvents":"Suffered a direct cannon attack from an enemy fighter, resulting in structural damage and casualties. The crew survived thanks to anti-spalling bulkheads.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Belt's communication networks"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Holden's next destination"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Docked at Thoth Station"}]},{"name":"Nauvoo","aliases":["Generation Ship"],"description":"A massive, half-built generation ship under construction at Tycho Station, serving as a potential vessel for interstellar travel.","recentEvents":"Miller observes its construction and meets Naomi to discuss comm data. He later connects with Havelock via a secure drop site.","relationships":[{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Under construction within Tycho Station's habitat rings"}]},{"name":"Guy Molinari","description":"A military assault ship used to breach Thoth Station during the OPA's coordinated attack.","recentEvents":"Miller and OPA forces launched a breach operation from the Guy Molinari, engaging Protogen security and navigating Thoth Station's defenses.","relationships":[{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Target of the assault"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Fred Johnson","Miller","Holden"],"summary":"Fred Johnson offers Miller a security consultant role to manage protomolecule containment, revealing OPA's desperation to control the crisis while navigating political tensions between Earth, Mars, and the Belt."},{"name":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Fred Johnson","Juliette Mao"],"summary":"Miller confronts his past actions and moral ambiguity as he accepts a role in OPA's containment strategy, balancing his guilt over Dresden's death with a new mission to secure Eros Station against protomolecule spread."},{"name":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Sam"],"summary":"Holden grapples with guilt over crew losses and the OPA's role in the war, while Naomi's romantic overture offers fleeting hope amid the looming threat of Earth-Mars conflict."},{"name":"Thoth Station Assault and Protomolecule Spread","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Amos","OPA soldiers","Jim Holden","Detective Miller"],"summary":"The protomolecule's spread from Thoth Station continues to threaten containment efforts, forcing Holden's crew to prioritize escape while OPA's bioweapon control faces escalating risks from Eros Station's instability."}],"summary":"Miller, grappling with his past actions and isolation, seeks employment on Ceres and Tycho Station. He confronts Fred Johnson about the protomolecule's threat on Eros Station, proposing its destruction to prevent global catastrophe. The narrative highlights the escalating danger of the protomolecule and its potential to reshape humanity."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":49,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao","Juliette Mao"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A captured crew member held in a storage locker, enduring eight days of isolation and dehydration while planning her escape. She discovers the ship's reactor has been replaced with an alien entity.","relationships":[{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile","relationship":"Family"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Former associate, now present at Thoth Station"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in internal dialogue with Miller about his past actions and future"},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Julie's shipmate and mechanic, who begged the captors not to take Julie before being thrown out an airlock.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Begged captors to spare Julie, was thrown out an airlock, and died."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Engineering deck","description":"The ship's captain who surrendered to the attackers without resistance, later found as a head fused to the alien reactor.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain"}],"recentEvents":"Surrendered to attackers, died after being part of the alien entity's fusion reactor."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate captured by the attackers along with others.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the attackers and taken off the ship."},{"name":"The Attackers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captors who took control of the ship, beat the crew, and sealed the ship's systems.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captors"}],"recentEvents":"Captured the crew, sealed the ship, and replaced the reactor with an alien entity."},{"name":"Jim Holden [aliases: James Holden, Holden]","aliases":["James Holden","Holden","Jim Holden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Commander of the Rocinante, involved in a romantic encounter with Naomi Nagata and a critical mission discussion with Fred Johnson and Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Close ally, whose perspective influences Holden's decisions"},{"character":"Ade Tukunbo","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Former commanding officer"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate and engineer"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate and weapons expert"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Captain Theresa Yao","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Debates with Miller about broadcasting the protomolecule data"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate and former detective"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Mission collaborator"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a romantic relationship with Naomi, discussed the plan to destroy Eros with Fred and Miller, and secured the protomolecule on the Rocinante."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata [aliases: Naomi]","aliases":["Naomi","Naomi Nagata"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Medical officer who tends to Miller and Holden. Engages in a tense conversation with Holden about his feelings for her.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and romantic interest"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Fought alongside during ambush"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate and former detective"},{"character":"Detecty Miller","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Mission collaborator"}],"recentEvents":"Had a romantic encounter with Holden, discussed the protomolecule's storage, and participated in the Eros mission planning."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Earthborn assistant to Naomi Nagata. Known for his loud personality and loyalty to Naomi.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Companion on the mission"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Visited Miller's cabin, shared breakfast, and discussed the war's impact"}],"recentEvents":"Received orders from Holden to secure the protomolecule on the Rocinante."},{"name":"Shed Garvey","aliases":["Shed"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Medical tech responsible for treating injured crew members. Known for using medical maggots in procedures.","relationships":[{"character":"Cameron Paj","relationship":"Patient"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned by Holden as someone he wished was still alive."},{"name":"Cameron Paj","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Crew member who lost his left arm in an ice-related accident. Uses a prosthetic limb.","relationships":[{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Implied to have an injured arm, mentioned by Shed during the aftermath."},{"name":"Ade Tukunbo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Navigator with a Nigerian accent and a fondness for music. Has a flirtatious relationship with Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Romantic interest"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to power up the Knight's drive, survived the nuke blast, communicated with Holden during the crisis."},{"name":"Rebecca Byers","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter One: Holden","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"Comm officer with a sharp appearance and a history of legal troubles. Handles emergency communications.","relationships":[{"character":"Captain McDowell","relationship":"Subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Received and relayed the emergency signal from an unknown ship."},{"name":"Captain McDowell","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"Commanding officer of the Canterbury. A grizzled veteran with a distrust of corrective surgery.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Former subordinate"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Holden instructions for the broadcast operation"},{"name":"Detective Miller [aliases: Miller]","aliases":["Miller","Detective Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Experienced security officer with a troubled past, investigating Julie Mao's disappearance while navigating political tensions between Mars, the Belt, and Earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Dmitri Havelock","relationship":"Former partner"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","relationship":"Former romantic partner"},{"character":"Havelock","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Octavia Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Subject of investigation"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"Dawes","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Inspector Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain of the Rocinante, debates with Miller about broadcasting the protomolecule data"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Aboard the Rocinante, with whom Miller discusses ethical dilemmas"},{"character":"Sematimba","relationship":"Contacted police"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Team member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Military contact seeking his expertise"},{"character":"Juliette Mao","relationship":"Former lover and partner in crime"}],"recentEvents":"Proposed the Eros destruction plan, mediated the conflict between Holden and Fred, and coordinated security for the mission."},{"name":"Captain Shaddid","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Commander of Star Helix Security on Ceres, known for her pragmatic approach and disdain for inner planet residents.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Subordinate"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Superior"},{"character":"OPA","relationship":"Leadership of the OPA's security apparatus"}],"recentEvents":"Announced the execution of Martian spies via a public video feed, emphasizing the OPA's stance on security"},{"name":"Alex Kamal","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Crewmate and engineer, skeptical of Martian involvement in the Canterbury's destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander and crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crew member and tactical operator"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Shed Garvey","relationship":"Crew member"},{"character":"Kelly","relationship":"Crewmate (deceased)"},{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Received orders from Holden to secure the protomolecule on the Rocinante."},{"name":"Dmitri Havelock [aliases: Havelock]","aliases":["Havelock","Dmitri Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ganymede server cluster","description":"Miller's partner and fellow security officer, who agrees to cover for Miller's absence while he investigates Julie Mao's case.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Former partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner who covers for Miller's absence"},{"character":"Captain Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided encrypted intel on Thoth Station's location to Miller."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Blue Frog (Ceres Station)","description":"Assistant manager of the Blue Frog, a portside bar on Ceres, who interacted with Detective Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informal acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Accompanied Miller home after a drinking session, revealed his feelings for Julie Mao."},{"name":"Brown","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, leading crowd control wings.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Part of Miller's riot squad, led during the mob confrontation."},{"name":"Gelbfish","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with SWAT experience, part of Miller's team.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Identified the shirtless man's OPA tattoo, participated in crowd control."},{"name":"Aberforth","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Security officer with a history of excessive violence, placed in second-string role.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Assigned to secondary roles due to past disciplinary issues."},{"name":"Yevgeny","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Homicide detective who commented on government offices during the crisis.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned the government's infrastructure status during Shaddid's briefing."},{"name":"Shirtless Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A former suspect in a crime, now in Star Helix detainment infirmary preparing for trial.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Ceres Station's ongoing legal cases"},{"name":"OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"An OPA representative with a pock-marked face, engaged in a tense conversation with Miller about OPA's role.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA contact"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's economic terrorism claims, denied involvement in Mateo Judd's death, and warned Miller to stay away."},{"name":"Wallace Fitz","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Saturn Station","description":"P and K legal counsel who issued formal orders to Holden and his crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Legal contact"}],"recentEvents":"Delivered official response to Holden's request for assistance, accused Holden of unfounded Martian accusations."},{"name":"Captain Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Commander of the Donnager, a Martian capital ship, overseeing the interrogation of Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Debriefed by Martian naval officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered the torpedo launch against the Belt ships and interrogated Holden about the pursuing vessels."},{"name":"Masked Woman","aliases":["Woman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Victim beaten to death by the shirtless man, identified as a Martian freight line employee.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Featured in Miller's terminal screen as part of OPA propaganda"},{"name":"Mateo Judd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Ten: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A dockworker accused of running an extortion scheme, later found dead with OPA ties.","relationships":[{"character":"Asher Kamamatsu","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Sought protection from the OPA, was killed by OPA operatives after Miller's investigation."},{"name":"Lieutenant Lopez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Naval intelligence officer conducting an interrogation of Holden, using focus drugs to monitor his responses.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Interrogated by naval intelligence"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a detailed interrogation of Holden, discussed the political tensions between Mars and the Belt, and fled to the combat zone after the torpedo attack."},{"name":"Chief Gunderson","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eleven: Holden","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Martian military chief responsible for escorting Holden's crew to their quarters.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Escorted to quarters"}],"recentEvents":"Led Holden's crew to their temporary accommodations and coordinated with Lieutenant Kelly for their protection."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["Dawes"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Sixteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"OPA liaison who approaches Detective Miller to stop his investigation into Julie Mao's disappearance, claiming it could escalate tensions between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"OPA agent attempting to dissuade Miller from pursuing a kidnapping case"}],"recentEvents":"Argued against Miller's investigation, claimed Holden's capture, and emphasized corporate neutrality."},{"name":"The Jiu Jitsu Instructor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twelve: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of the Ceres Center for Jiu Jitsu, who provides limited information about Julie Mao's background and training.","relationships":[]},{"name":"Enrique Dos Santos","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fourteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Tortured and displayed near sector eleven's water reclamation works; identified by terminal, wedding ring, and credit data"},{"name":"Octavia Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A pragmatic detective who handles interrogations and provides Miller with critical case updates.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Colleague"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Partner"},{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Superior"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a rape case witness detail, skipped work to attend to a stop, and observed the political upheaval on Ceres."},{"name":"Kelly","aliases":["Lieutenant Kelly"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tachi","description":"Deceased marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Died from severe injuries during the battle, then buried by the crew."},{"name":"Gomez","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Fifteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Marine who died during the battle on the Donnager.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Killed by enemy fire while defending the Donnager."},{"name":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station detention cells","description":"A businessman arrested for rape, portrayed as a high-profile client with connections to influential war effort figures.","relationships":[{"character":"Harry","relationship":"Lawyer"}],"recentEvents":"Detained under a warrant following a rape investigation, confronted by Detective Miller, and subjected to legal scrutiny."},{"name":"Harry","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd's lawyer, who warns Miller of potential legal repercussions for his investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Immanuel Corvus Dowd","relationship":"Client"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to shield his client from arrest, engaged in tense dialogue with Miller, and exited the interrogation room."},{"name":"Young Woman in Cream-Colored Linen","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Eighteen: Miller","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A professional-looking woman who briefly acknowledged Miller before entering the accountancy office.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nodded to Miller as he left the accountancy office, displaying a calm, fighter-like demeanor."},{"name":"Bartender","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Singer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Teenage Girls","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Nineteen: Holden","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","relationships":[]},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros hotel room","description":"A fictional person Fred Johnson claims to need retrieved from Eros, owning the courier ship Scopuli.","relationships":[{"character":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","relationship":"Target of retrieval"}],"recentEvents":"Targeted by Holden's group, last seen in his hotel room."},{"name":"Missionary","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"A traveling missionary with a name tag and Bible","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Engaging in philosophical conversation about religion and war with Miller"},{"name":"Inspector Sematimba","aliases":["Sematimba"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Six: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Police officer who imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Contacted for police assistance"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Enforced lockdown"}],"recentEvents":"Imposed a lockdown on Holden's ship, communicated with Miller about jurisdictional concerns."},{"name":"Woman with the gun","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros flophouse","description":"Armed assailant who confronted Holden's group.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed during the confrontation at Lionel Polanski's flophouse."},{"name":"Guard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A fake riot cop leading civilians to a radiation shelter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Nudged by Miller after the shootout."},{"name":"Gabby Smalls","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Seven: Holden","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A mobster and police riot gear supervisor on Ceres, leading civilians to shelters.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as a key figure in the Ceres protection racket."},{"name":"Mikey Ko","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Eight: Miller","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A guard who mistook Miller and Holden for Protogen installers, leading to his death at Miller's hands.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's lethal action"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Witness to Miller's confrontation"}],"recentEvents":"Was killed by Miller after revealing details about Protogen's operations on Eros."},{"name":"Mafia Thug","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A violent enforcer killed by Holden during a mob incident.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Holden after firing on civilians."},{"name":"Child Victim","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Twenty-Nine: Holden","currentLocation":"Eros station","description":"A thirteen-year-old boy killed by the mafia thug during the chaos on Eros station.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died from a gunshot wound to the chest, rescued by Holden."},{"name":"Mr. Dresden","aliases":["sociopath","Dresden"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A former Protogen scientist and antagonist, killed by Miller during the Thoth Station incident.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Victim of Miller's actions"}],"recentEvents":"Shot and killed by Miller, with his corpse serving as a catalyst for moral conflict."},{"name":"Captain Higgins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Thirty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Commander of a ship infected by a lethal alien pathogen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Sent a final distress message about crew casualties and the ship's condition before losing contact."},{"name":"Fred Johnson [aliases: Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson, Colonel Johnson]","aliases":["Fred Johnson","Colonel Frederick Lucius Johnson","Colonel Johnson"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Five: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Colonel and leader of the Outer Planets Alliance, contacting Holden about potential Martian threats.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Military contact seeking his expertise"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Commander of the Rocinante"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Business associate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Business associate"}],"recentEvents":"Argued with Holden over the protomolecule's handling, approved the Eros destruction plan, and mediated between Holden and Miller."},{"name":"Diogo","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A Belter and friend of Miller, providing a temporary place to stay.","relationships":[{"character":"Detective Miller","relationship":"Informant and potential employer"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with a job opportunity and discussed Eros Station's mysterious broadcasts"},{"name":"OPA soldiers","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Two: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Members of the OPA involved in the Thoth Station occupation.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Present during the shooting of Dresden, surprised by the violence."},{"name":"Sam","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Three: Holden","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"Team leader on the Rocinante repair project, known for her mechanical skills and dry humor","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Respects her work on the Rocinante"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Friendly rivalry and camaraderie"}],"recentEvents":"Completed critical repairs on the Rocinante, engaged in banter with Holden and Naomi about the Golgo game"},{"name":"Manager","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter Forty-Four: Miller","currentLocation":"Thoth Station","description":"A weedy, disheveled office manager in Tycho Station","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Rejected Miller's job application for a security guard position"}],"locations":[{"name":"Scopuli","arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A stealth ship captured and repurposed, later found to be infected with a deadly biological agent.","recentEvents":"The ship's crew was killed by an unknown pathogen, with Julie Mao's body remaining in an unsealed locker.","relationships":[{"location":"Engineering deck","relationship":"Contains the ship's reactor and is the site of critical discoveries"},{"location":"Inner airlock","relationship":"Where Julie was initially confined and later accessed after escaping"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was transported here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"The ship's contamination and events on Eros are interconnected."}]},{"name":"Engineering deck","aliases":["Engineering deck"],"arc":"Julie's Survival and Escape","description":"The ship's core area housing the fusion reactor and critical systems.","recentEvents":"Julie discovers the reactor's corrupted state, with biological material fused to its core. Captain Darren's head is found here.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Central operational area of the ship"}]},{"name":"Inner airlock","aliases":["Inner airlock"],"description":"A sealed compartment connecting different sections of the ship.","recentEvents":"Julie was confined here for eight days before escaping. It served as a transition point between decks.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Structural component of the ship"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["Knight","Knight-class ship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A P and K shuttle craft carrying Jim Holden and his crew after the Canterbury's destruction.","recentEvents":"Holden's crew was boarded by Martian marines after docking, leading to an interrogation by Lieutenant Lopez and a tense standoff with approaching Belt ships.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Travels between Saturn's rings and this region"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Adjacent spaceport for departure/arrival"},{"location":"CA-2216862","relationship":"Target location for salvage mission"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Docked at the Donnager's docking bay"}]},{"name":"Belt","aliases":["Asteroid Belt"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"The region of space where the Canterbury and other ships operate, containing numerous asteroids and debris.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury was destroyed here by a nuclear weapon fired by a stealth ship. Holden and the Knight crew pursued the attackers while hiding behind an asteroid.","relationships":[{"location":"Callisto","relationship":"Adjacent to a charted non-Belt asteroid"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Destroyed in this region"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Survived here after the Canterbury's destruction"}]},{"name":"Callisto","description":"A non-Belt asteroid where a damaged Martian freighter sent an emergency signal.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury diverted its route to investigate the distress beacon near this location.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located near the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres Port","Ceres"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A major Belt station and economic hub, home to six million people. Serves as a critical node in the conflict between Mars and the Belt.","recentEvents":"The OPA announced the execution of Martian spies via an industrial airlock, framing it as a necessary action for freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Central to Ceres' economic role as a transit point for Belt resources"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Connected via trade routes and shared security concerns"},{"location":"Port Level","relationship":"Key area where the riot occurs"},{"location":"Station House","relationship":"Administrative center where security directives are issued"},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Site of the Black Cat freighter's destination after transferring stolen riot gear"},{"location":"Io","relationship":"Destination of the perps who disposed of the murder weapon"},{"location":"Star Helix","relationship":"Former governing authority now withdrawn"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Martian warship whose destruction triggered the Belt's uprising"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden and Miller discuss the protomolecule's data here"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation (Fred Johnson's Role Revealed)","description":"Corporate station serving as a hub between the Belt and inner planets, known for its interplanetary transport operations.","recentEvents":"Miller returned to Tycho after Thoth, where he encountered fellow Thoth survivors and witnessed decrypted footage of the protomolecule's transformation of Eros.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Serves as a key waypoint for cargo and passenger traffic between the Belt and inner systems"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked by the Belt's orbital pathways"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Holden's destination after leaving the ship"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Miller's temporary base after leaving Thoth"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Protomolecule activity was decrypted from Eros feeds"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","aliases":["Asteroid 2216862"],"description":"A half-kilometer-wide asteroid in the asteroid belt, serving as a gravitational anchor for the Scopuli.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli was deliberately positioned near this asteroid, likely to exploit its microgravity for slow orbital capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Gravitational anchor point"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Located within the asteroid belt"}]},{"name":"Port Level","description":"A bustling industrial area of Ceres Station where ships dock and cargo is handled, marked by high gravity and constant activity.","recentEvents":"Miller's squad confronts a violent mob, including an OPA-linked killer, to prevent the riot from escalating.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"A distinct sector within the station"}]},{"name":"MCRN Donnager","aliases":["Donnager","Martian battleship"],"arc":"OPA's Role in the Martian-Belt War","description":"A massive Martian capital ship with a stark, utilitarian design, serving as a military base for Martian forces.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden investigate the ship's engineering deck, discovering signs of a violent takeover and the presence of a mysterious infectious agent.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn Station","relationship":"Origin of the order"},{"location":"Jupiter","relationship":"Destination for the Knight"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Hosted the docking and interrogation of the Knight"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Engaged in combat with Belt ships following a torpedo launch"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"The Scopuli's crew was captured and held here before their deaths."},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Events on Eros Station are linked to the ship's contamination and the crew's fate."}]},{"name":"Saturn Station","aliases":["Saturn Station"],"description":"A Martian-controlled space station where P and K legal counsel issued directives.","recentEvents":"Wallace Fitz communicated the order to head to Jupiter, escalating tensions with Mars.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Source of the crew's orders"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Previously mentioned in crew discussions"}]},{"name":"Jupiter","aliases":["Jupiter"],"description":"A gas giant and strategic destination for the Knight crew's flight path.","recentEvents":"Selected as a potential destination despite risks from unknown pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Geographically adjacent region"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Target location for the ship"}]},{"name":"Razorback","aliases":["Razorback"],"description":"A private racing vessel associated with the Mao family, symbolizing Julie Mao's past and the family's financial influence.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's messages reveal her family's attempt to coerce her to return, referencing the ship's potential sale and its significance to her.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Razorback is mentioned as a vessel tied to the Mao family's operations on Ceres."}]},{"name":"Anderson Station","aliases":["Anderson"],"description":"A minor Belt distribution station for water and air, infamous for the Massacre that made Fred Johnson a Belter hero.","recentEvents":"Fred Johnson's broadcast reveals the station's history as a site of Coalition brutality, framing it as a catalyst for OPA resistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt's contested regions"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Johnson's message hints at potential Martian involvement in the current conflict"}]},{"name":"Phoebe Station","aliases":["Phoebe"],"description":"A science station in the asteroid belt, forbidden for Belters to dock at.","recentEvents":"Destroyed in an attack attributed to Belter guerrilla groups, with half its inhabitants dead or missing.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via Belt political tensions"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","aliases":["Hangar"],"description":"A section of the Donnager containing multiple ships, including the Knight, where the crew attempts to escape.","recentEvents":"The crew fought through boarders to reach a corvette, with Lieutenant Kelly leading the evacuation.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Part of the ship's structure"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"A ship stationed in the bay"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","description":"A moon with significant mining and trade operations in the Jupiter system.","recentEvents":"The Black Cat freighter, linked to stolen riot gear, made a stop here after departing Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Io","arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"A volcanic moon in Jupiter's system, often used as a transit point for illicit operations.","recentEvents":"The perps who disposed of the murder weapon and stolen gear were headed here, though their arrival remains uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Black Cat's transit route"}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Martian Congressional Republic"],"arc":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","description":"Planet at the center of a conflict with the Belt, governed by the Martian Congressional Republic.","recentEvents":"The Martian Congressional Republic declared open war against the Belt, citing security threats and economic sabotage, escalating tensions across the system.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Region in armed conflict with Mars"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Site of growing unrest due to the war's proximity"}]},{"name":"Pallas","aliases":["Pallas Station"],"description":"A celestial body in the asteroid belt, serving as a transit hub for freighters and prospectors.","recentEvents":"The Adrianopole, a third-gen prospector, docked here after arriving from the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via freighter routes and political tensions"}]},{"name":"Luna","description":"Earth's moon, a key node in interplanetary trade and military operations.","recentEvents":"The Badass Motherfucker freighter operated a triangle route between Luna, Ganymede, and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Connected via the Badass Motherfucker's trade route"},{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Part of a regional trade network"}]},{"name":"Triton","description":"Neptune's largest moon, home to deep astronomy labs repurposed by OPA-aligned prospectors.","recentEvents":"Prospectors sympathetic to the OPA occupied the labs, broadcasting Martian ship locations.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Linked to OPA operations and resource conflicts"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Target of data broadcasts revealing Martian military assets"}]},{"name":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","aliases":["Eros","Eros Station","Maintenance Tunnel","Maintenance Shaft","Eros flophouse","Eros station"],"arc":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","description":"A dimly lit service passage carved by early Belters, housing critical power lines and running through the first Belt colony's infrastructure.","recentEvents":"Miller listens to dying system voices from Eros, discussing the protomolecule's effects and its potential to spread. Fred Johnson considers destroying Eros to prevent its proliferation.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Part of the Belt's interconnected stations"},{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Ship associated with the deceased Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Home port of the freighter the Canterbury is responding to"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Linked via OPA operations and the broader Belt conflict"},{"location":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","relationship":"Adjacent to the maintenance corridors"},{"location":"Casino Level","relationship":"Part of the lockdown area"},{"location":"MCRN Donnager","relationship":"Miller and Holden were rescued from Eros Station by the Donnager"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's utility infrastructure"},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Miller's temporary residence before departing"},{"location":"Protogen","relationship":"Site of the protomolecule's initial deployment"},{"location":"OPA","relationship":"Target of Protogen's operations"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Protomolecule activity was revealed through Eros feeds"}]},{"name":"BA834024112","aliases":["Rock BA834024112","Julie's asteroid"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A barren asteroid tethered to a wealthy owner, serving as a navigational warning.","recentEvents":"Holden and the crew of the Rocinante approach it, discovering a stealth ship linked to the Donnager's destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Linked to the shuttle that carried Julie and may hide the ship's remnants"},{"location":"Phoebe Station","relationship":"The Phoebe bug originated from this science station, connecting to Julie's infection"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"The Rocinante is en route to Ceres after analyzing data from this asteroid."}]},{"name":"Casino Level","aliases":["Radiological Shelter","Casino Area"],"description":"A restricted zone on Eros Station where the population is funneled during lockdowns, serving as a central gathering point.","recentEvents":"The level is under lockdown, with guards enforcing movement toward shelters. Miller and Holden use this as a strategic point to regroup.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Part of the station's structure"}]},{"name":"Radiation Shelters (Eros Station)","aliases":["Radiation Lockdown Zones","Radiation Incubators"],"description":"Sealed-off sections of Eros Station purportedly designed to protect citizens from radiation, but secretly used as containment areas for lethal gas and biological agents.","recentEvents":"The shelters were emptied, leaving only Holden and Miller's footsteps. Ko's body is left here after being shot.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Designated emergency lockdown zones"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via transit corridors"},{"location":"Eros Station Maintenance Corridor","relationship":"Located nearby"}]},{"name":"Thoth Station","aliases":["Thoth"],"arc":"Thoth Station Assault and Protomolecule Spread","description":"A space station where Captain Higgins sent a distress message about the deteriorating condition of his crew and secured materials before the ship's fate.","recentEvents":"Miller executed captured Protogen scientist Dresden in cold blood, sparking tension with Holden. OPA forces skeletonized the station before evacuating it, revealing the protomolecule's presence in hidden feeds.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"The ship's location is being tracked in the Belt, as per the comm log."},{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"The comm log was received on the Rocinante, which is now searching for the ship."},{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Linked via secure server cluster"},{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via OPA operations"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Miller is now stationed here after leaving Thoth"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Protomolecule activity was decrypted from Eros feeds"}]},{"name":"Rocinante","aliases":["Roci"],"arc":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","description":"A private ship used by the crew, serving as their mobile base of operations.","recentEvents":"Suffered a direct cannon attack from an enemy fighter, resulting in structural damage and casualties. The crew survived thanks to anti-spalling bulkheads.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres Station","relationship":"Linked via the Belt's communication networks"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Holden's next destination"},{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Docked at Thoth Station"}]},{"name":"Nauvoo","aliases":["Generation Ship"],"description":"A massive, half-built generation ship under construction at Tycho Station, serving as a potential vessel for interstellar travel.","recentEvents":"Miller observes its construction and meets Naomi to discuss comm data. He later connects with Havelock via a secure drop site.","relationships":[{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Under construction within Tycho Station's habitat rings"}]},{"name":"Guy Molinari","description":"A military assault ship used to breach Thoth Station during the OPA's coordinated attack.","recentEvents":"Miller and OPA forces launched a breach operation from the Guy Molinari, engaging Protogen security and navigating Thoth Station's defenses.","relationships":[{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Target of the assault"}]},{"name":"Charles Lyell","aliases":["Earth science vessel"],"description":"A science vessel deployed by Earth to investigate Eros, accompanied by a Phantom-class escort ship.","recentEvents":"Holden and Fred discuss the Lyell's approach to Eros and the risk of it recovering protomolecule samples.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Target of the Lyell's mission"},{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Protomolecule sample is believed to be on this station"}]},{"name":"Phantom-class escort ship","description":"An older Earth military ship class used to accompany science vessels like the Charles Lyell.","recentEvents":"Part of the Lyell's fleet, tasked with protecting its mission to Eros.","relationships":[{"location":"Charles Lyell","relationship":"Companion ship"},{"location":"Eros Station","relationship":"Potential threat to the protomolecule sample"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"OPA's Bioweapon Containment and Strategic Manipulation","status":"active","characters":["Fred Johnson","Miller","Holden"],"summary":"Fred Johnson offers Miller a security consultant role to manage protomolecule containment, revealing OPA's desperation to control the crisis while navigating political tensions between Earth, Mars, and the Belt."},{"name":"Miller's Moral Conflict and Tactical Engagement","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Fred Johnson","Juliette Mao"],"summary":"Miller confronts his past actions and moral ambiguity as he accepts a role in OPA's containment strategy, balancing his guilt over Dresden's death with a new mission to secure Eros Station against protomolecule spread."},{"name":"Holden's Crew Survival and Escape","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Sam"],"summary":"Holden grapples with guilt over crew losses and the OPA's role in the war, while Naomi's romantic overture offers fleeting hope amid the looming threat of Earth-Mars conflict."},{"name":"Thoth Station Assault and Protomolecule Spread","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Amos","OPA soldiers","Jim Holden","Detective Miller"],"summary":"The protomolecule's spread from Thoth Station continues to threaten containment efforts, forcing Holden's crew to prioritize escape while OPA's bioweapon control faces escalating risks from Eros Station's instability."}],"summary":"Holden and Naomi navigate political tensions with Fred Johnson over the protomolecule's fate while planning to destroy Eros using the Nauvoo's trajectory and explosive traps. The Earth science vessel Charles Lyell poses a new threat, forcing Holden to balance loyalty to his crew with the risk 